mplicitly hierarchical naming convention developed for tender codes for }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736 use with }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid6379056 reason codes}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736  also}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid6379056 .}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid13914681 \r\n\\par }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://pcats.org/node/680\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid931402\\charrsid931402 POS/BO Minutes 2007-05-15}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\r\n\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid6379056  }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid931402 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid6379056 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid6379056 Discussion of the feedback from the EPS group.\r\n\\par The name (e.g. VISA) is a \"circuit code\" and is provided by the host system.\r\n\\par EPS group send a \"circuit code\" to identify the type of payment.\r\n\\par Discussion on should we remove the \"Circuit code\" from the tenderCode enumerated list.\r\n\\par Proposal is that the POS will receive the circuit code from the EPS and map that to a POS Tender. The POS will then map that to a tenderCode. Additionally we may add the circuit code data to the tender element in the sales transaction (POS Journal).\r\n\r\n\\par Meeting resolved to respond to the EPS group that we plan to keep our MOP categorization scheme and add the ability to pass Tender configuration to the POS from the BOS which will allow mapping of circuit codes to tenders. Rational: Our customers\\rquote \r\n needs for Tender categorization will not always map exactly to Circuit Codes.\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid6379056 \r\nDavid Ezell to review the IFSF circuit codes and check that they can be accommodated in the tenderCodes.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid6379056\\charrsid6379056 \r\n\\par }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/node/831\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid13914681\\charrsid1118518 POS/BO Minutes 2007-08-07}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\r\n\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid13914681 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid6379056 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid6379056 \r\nWe agreed that issue 188 will be used to track the adoption of the enumerated tender code and circuit code\r\n\\par Circuit code will be a sub element of nax:authorization block since it is some\r\nthing returned from the host and not credit processor dependant. It is also separate from the tender. Placing the new tag here will allow circuit code to be reported on separately from the tender or in combination with the tender.\r\n\\par New issue created (223) to track the adoption of a tender code maintenance document with updates to PJR. \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/node/1040\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid9514677\\charrsid9514677 POS/BO Minutes 2007-12-05}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid10174327 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\nMr. Wade recommended that currency codes available for use at the POS be incorporated into the site conf\r\niguration document. Currency exchange rates, min/max amounts and other data related to the POS usage of currency could be communicated separately, possibly via Tender configuration.\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://pcats.org/node/1086\"}\r\n}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid13914681\\charrsid13914681 POS/BO Minutes 2008-01-21}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid13914681 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid10174327 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\nDiscussion of CR188: A large multi-national retailer has requested a tender configuration document.\\~ Their proposal is fairly complex.\\~\r\n The committee has previously decided to create a simpler tender configuration document that permits the association of n\r\network circuit codes (a more specific identifier for a credit tender, e.g. Visa Debit from XYS Bank of Wellington NZ) to POS tender codes.\\~ The group reaffirmed that decision.\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/node/1560\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid1118518\\charrsid1118518 POS/BO Minutes 2008-05-08}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid1118518 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid10174327 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 Coupon processing}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \r\n\\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 Accounting}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par Coupons are handled as an open receivable.\\~\\~\\~ Reimbursed as a face value and then the manufacturer and reimburse the retailer for 8 cents for handling the coupon.\\~\\~\\~ Typically, store coupons are not reimbursed but the amount and barcode\r\ns are kept track of.\\~\\~\\~ Double coupons are handled by the retailer but only the face value is reimbursed.\\~\\~ \r\n\\par David asked whether we should handle this as a tender?\\~ He asked that of the group.\\~\\~\\~ Lisa stated that this varies from store to store either a discount or a tender.\r\n\\par Bill stated would it be best to know which items a coupon applies to and apply the discount appropriately that would be good but we want to also handle this as an A/R.\\~\\~\\~\\~ Need to determine which item is affected by the coupon.\\~\\~ Net of\r\n item associated with a coupon need to match A/R.\\~\\~\\~ Need to determine whether this is a standard discount or whether it should be handled another way.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 What is being scanned?}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par Company Prefix\r\n\\par Manufacturer\'s ID\r\n\\par Family Code\\~ (Associates to particular products)\r\n\\par GS1 data bar code (Betty Lou Vonsolos) is an expert in the new GS1 barcode.\\~\\~ (RSS renamed) by Bill Wade must be used by 2010 for the new standard.\r\n\\par Store can use the new bar code (GS1) for in store coupons immediately.\\~\\~\\~\\~ Better validation than in the old code.\\~ They ran out of Manufacturer IDs so that they needed more room for those codes.\\~ Up to 128 bytes of data in a GS1 barcode.\r\n\\par There is a spec on the GS1 web site for this.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 POS Setup}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par Store coupons need to be handled as items but manufacturer coupons need to be configured in the POS.\\~\\~\\~ \r\n\\par Need to know if merchants want to support Manufacturer coupons and whether an item is eligible for a coupon or not.\\~\\~\\~ That is done with a family code match.\\~\\~\\~\\~ \r\n\\par Whether or not to accept Manufacturer coupons?\\~\\~\\~\\~ Does this need to be a setting for the POS?\r\n\\par Two sources of family codes-a fee based information service.\\~\\~ The POS would have to have a family code associated with everything sold.\\~\\~\\~\\~\\~ This would be entered in the backoffice in the item maintenance in the family code.\\~\\~\\~\r\n POS accepts these though the pricebook.\\~\\~ \r\n\\par Today\'s situation is likely that coupons are dependent on the cashier doing this manually.\r\n\\par Gregg stated that the Pantry uses to collect coupons and he will follow up on how they handle the coupons.\\~ \r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 Taxable vs. non taxable coupons.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \\~\\~ Kelly will research.\\~\\~ \r\n\\par Types of coupons?\\~\\~ Manufacture or store coupon?\\~\\~\\~ Handled the same way as Manufacturer coupons.\\~\\~\\~ Redemption agency can supply marketing information for the retailer.\\~\r\n It will be helpful to keep data the same for both manufacturer and store coupons.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 Electronic coupon redemption...}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par There is a one count process but tor cigarettes, manufacturers require the physical coupon.\\~ \r\n\\par 80% or the Convenience Store coupon volume is tobacco some in drinks etc...\\~ So it is likely that the manual process would be used for convenience store coupon redemption.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs24\\b\\ul\\cf1\\insrsid10174327 Double coupons}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10174327 \r\n\\par Double coupons are handled the same way are manufacturer coupons by the processor.\\~\\~ They only invoice what is on the coupon.\\~\\~\\~ The rest of the cost is on the retailer.\r\n\\par Kelly to double check on this....\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/node/1941\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid9514677\\charrsid9514677 POS/BO Minutes 2008-08-18}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9514677 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid5378622 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 CR215 - The use case for distinguishing forgiven taxes fr\r\nom exempted taxes is that tax is forgiven on items purchased by the consumer using government benefits, e.g. food stamps or electronic benefits.\\~ Tax is forgiven only on those items eligible for purchase with those tenders.\\~\r\n The members present were unaware of any requirements governing the reporting of forgiven tax amounts to the appropriate tax authorities.\\~ When the POS calculates the amount of tax to forgive, it may take two approaches:\r\n\\par 1) Calculate tax at the transaction level, and forgive the amount of tax applicable to the value of the government-issued tender provided, or \r\n\\par 2) Calculate tax at the item level, and forgive tax on eligible items whose combined value does not exceed the value of the government-issued tender provided, but in no case is only part of the tax on an item forgiven. \r\n\\par The POS requires a configuration option to determine whether to favor the state or the customer when forgiving taxes.\\~ When favoring the customer, the POS applies the tender to items with the highest tax burden first.\\~\r\n When favoring the state, the POS applies taxes to items with the lowest tax burden first.\\~ Which option is selected is determined by the regulations of the state in question.\r\n\\par The conclusion of the working group is that configuration data related to tax forgiveness is typically associated with the tender, rather than the tax.\\~\r\n The POS must to report the amount of forgiven taxes and tax-forgiven sales by tax level ID, and support for the favor state/favor customer flag should be included when tender configuration is implemented.\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s4\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sb200\\sl408\\slmult1\\keep\\keepn\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\outlinelevel3\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid5378622 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ab\\ai\\af31503\\afs22\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\b\\i\\fs22\\cf18\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\loch\\af31502\\hich\\af31502\\dbch\\af31501\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31503 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cf1\\insrsid5378622 \\hich\\af31502\\dbch\\af31501\\loch\\f31502 Coupons\r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid5378622 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f31506\\fs22\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 CR195 - The question with respect to this CR is whether it applies to the implementation of manufacturer coupons in addition to retailers own coupons.\\~\r\n Theoretically, a manufacturer coupon has a barcode that identifies the manufacturer ID, product family code, and face value.\\~\r\n However, the current coupon barcode structure is insufficient to support manufacturer codes longer than five digits, which GS1 began issuing effective January 1, 2005.\\~ Moreover, manufacturers have a desire to specify more data in their coupons.\\~\r\n For this reason, GS1 proffered a new coupon barcode standard based on the GS1 Databar standard (formerly named Reduced Space Symbology, or RSS).\\~ The new Databar standard supports the inclusion of more data rega\r\nrding product eligibility and coupon value.\\~ Retailers are free to begin implementing GS1 Database on their own coupons effective immediately (provided, of course, that their POS supports it).\\~\r\n GS1 has established a January 1, 2010 sunrise date for manufacturer implementation of the GS1 Databar standard for coupons.\r\n\\par Recognition and acceptance of manufacturer coupons at the POS level is predicated on the assumption that the POS can interpret the coupon barcode and determine whether a given transaction meets \r\nthe conditions encoded therein, without requiring the presence of the coupon barcode within the POS database.\\~ This requires the presence of the manufacturer\'s coupon family code on each of the items in the POS database.\\~\r\n Many convenience retailers do not have the family code within their pricebook, nor do they have ready access to that data, rendering POS validation of manufacturer coupons problematic.\\~\r\n Many retailers therefore rely on the cashier to visually validate the coupons.\r\n\\par Retailers may issue their own coupons.\\~ GS1 guidelines are available for in-store coupon barcodes, which many retailers do not follow.\\~\r\n Many retailers simply encode a PLU number on a coupon, and configure that PLU as a negative item that reduces the transaction amount.\\~ \r\n\\par Manufacturer coupons are typically treated as tenders, being applied post-tax.\\~ Retailer coupons are typically treated as discounts, being applied pre-tax.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 Mr. Ezell re-opened the discussion of coupons from the previous day by inviting Mr. Peele to recap the issues associated with coupons.\r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f3\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\loch\\af3\\dbch\\af31506\\hich\\f3 \\\'b7\\tab}}\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\s28\\ql \\fi-360\\li720\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\r\n\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\ls3\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0\\pararsid5378622\\contextualspace \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f31506\\fs22\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \r\n\\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 Two types of coupons - manufacturer-issued & retailer-issued \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f3\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\loch\\af3\\dbch\\af31506\\hich\\f3 \\\'b7\\tab}\r\nDiffering tax properties (manufacturer-issued coupons are typically post-tax (but not always - some states require pre-tax instead), retailer-issued coupons are typically pre-tax). Tax handling for coupons are typically handled via a flag on the associate\r\nd tender or item, indicating whether they affect tax. \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f3\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\loch\\af3\\dbch\\af31506\\hich\\f3 \\\'b7\\tab}\r\nImpending change from current UPC-A/UCC-128 barcodes to GS1 Databar, which may be problematic since the GS1 spec (at least per the Sep 2007 specification) does not call for the scanner to return a fixed\r\n-width value for the manufacturer code embedded in the barcode, which will make parsing out the manufacturer code and other values in the barcode problematic. \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f3\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\loch\\af3\\dbch\\af31506\\hich\\f3 \\\'b7\\tab}Retailers typically do not use the GS1 coupon barcode standards, because to do so would render t\r\nheir coupons indistinguishable from manufacturer coupons. Instead, retailers typically print a UPC-A barcode associated with a coupon-type item or negative item pre-configured on the POS. \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f3\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\loch\\af3\\dbch\\af31506\\hich\\f3 \\\'b7\\tab}If coupon items are downloaded to the POS via NAXML, they will requ\r\nire additional configuration, e.g.: }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af2\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f2\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\hich\\af2\\dbch\\af31506\\loch\\f2 o\\tab}}\\pard \\ltrpar\\s28\\ql \\fi-360\\li1440\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\r\n\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\ls3\\ilvl1\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin1440\\itap0\\pararsid5378622\\contextualspace {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 Amount or Percent Off Flag}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid5378622 \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af2\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f2\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\hich\\af2\\dbch\\af31506\\loch\\f2 o\\tab}}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 Amount or Percent Off}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \r\n\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af2\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f2\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\hich\\af2\\dbch\\af31506\\loch\\f2 o\\tab}}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \r\nMaximum number per transaction (this coupon)}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af2\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f2\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\hich\\af2\\dbch\\af31506\\loch\\f2 o\\tab}}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 Prompt for price flag \r\n\\par {\\listtext\\pard\\plain\\ltrpar \\s28 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af2\\afs22 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f2\\fs22\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \\hich\\af2\\dbch\\af31506\\loch\\f2 o\\tab}Some POS systems support automatically triggered \"coupon-less\" coupons for cigarette buydowns, which r\r\nequire the retailer to tax the cigarettes at the pre-buydown price. \r\n\\par }\\pard\\plain \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid5378622 \\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs22\\alang1025 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f31506\\fs22\\lang1033\\langfe1033\\cgrid\\langnp1033\\langfenp1033 {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\ai\\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\i\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \r\nBest practice note - retailer coupons downloaded to the POS as coupon-type or negative items should have taxes enabled to affect the discount pre-tax, and should have taxes disabled to affect the discount post-tax.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \r\n\\par Mr. Ezell noted that if tender maintenance is implemented, the circuit code for tender codes will need to be expanded to support retailer and manufacturer coupons.\r\n\\par If the GS-1 Coupon Databar specification does not provide a mechanism that permits the POS to}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622  distinguish}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \r\n retailer-issued from manufacturer-issued coupons, retailer may have to resort to using coupon items instead, depending on their business requirements.\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/node/2452\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid1118518\\charrsid1118518 POS/BO Minutes 2009-01-26}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid1118518 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid14974736 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \r\nTender Restrictions (can\'t purchase lottery tickets with credit cards }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 or cigarettes with food stamps).}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid5378622 \r\n\\par }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000083\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\in