 use with a given item if SalesRestriction is used instead of SalesR\r\nestrictCode.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736 Notes\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid14974736 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736 2007-08-04: Applies to MerchandiseCodes also.\r\n\r\n\\par 2008-08-11: There may be items like lottery, lotto, money orders that may be cash only items and not allowed to be purchased with other MOPs like credit cards.\r\n\\par }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000167\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid10492109\\charrsid14974736 CR167}}}\r\n\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736  - [New Data] Add support of local accounts prepayments and deposit payments}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \r\n\\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10492109\\charrsid14974736 \r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736 Description: Many POS systems support local account prepayments (received on account) and deposit payments. There should be a possibility to export these data to the backoffice.\r\n\\par Business Case: This feature is owned by the following TF:\\line Dave Egan\\line Gregg Peele\\line Lisa Hester\r\n\\par }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000186\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid10492109\\charrsid14974736 CR186}}}\r\n\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10492109\\charrsid14974736 \r\n\\par }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000188\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid1978834\\charrsid14974736 CR188}}}\r\n\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736  - }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\fs20\\cf1\\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736 \r\n[New Data] Add Coupon Maintenance and review journal treatment}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\fs20\\cf1\\insrsid9514677\\charrsid14974736 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9111078 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid14974736\\charrsid14974736 \r\nDescription: Add maintenance functions for Coupons and review their treatment in the Journal.\r\n\\par Business Case: Essentially the committee recognizes that there are two types of coupons -- those that can be used as tenders and those that act as discounts. We\'ll have to disentangle those issues.  This feature is owned by the following TF:\\line \r\nDave Egan\\line Gregg Peele\\line Lisa Hester\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid14974736 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622\\charrsid14974736 2007-06-07: Added new schema\\line \r\nImplementation Notes:\\line 1) Specific types yet to be assigned.\\line 2) For Flags:\\line \\~\\~\\~a) left out Group (key is to be a Tender-code, implying groups).\\line \\~\\~\\~b) do we really want to tie currencies to tenders?\\line \\~\\~\\~\r\nc) left off \"Print Signature Panel\"\\line \\~\\~\\~d) left off \"Button Bitmap\"\\line 3) what did we decide about circuit codes?\\line 4) what do we do about bunches of optional elements in the \"complete\" version\\line \\~\\~\\~of the complex type?\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid14974736 2008-06-07: Closing 187 as a duplicate\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid10500608 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\ul\\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Notes excerpted from CR187\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li720\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin720\\itap0\\pararsid10500608 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Summary:}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid10500608  Create Tender Configuration\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Description: Need to add the ability to define tenders and connect tender codes. Specifically need to assign circuit codes to tender codes.  }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Vaughn Hunt of Chevron has provided a presentation with a sugg}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 ested set of tender properties.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Business Case: This subject has proven too complex to be accommodated with a simple set of standard codes.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 \r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Note 2007-05-17: We have placed this item in the feedback state to allow review by members so that they can add suggestions to the\r\n Chevron suggestions.  Note that this dataset, like others, may not be settab}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 le, but should be queryable.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 Note 2007-08-04: Reassign to Configuration - Tender Codes document\\line However, the committee has assumed that the key field will be either the existing 4\r\n.0 tender code or a derivative (i.e. extension) of one of its members.}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608 \r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid10500608 {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid5378622 2007-06-20: Committee discussed that\\line \r\n1) minimum requirement is tenderCode plus CircuitCode, maybe description\\line 2) network circuit codes need to be assigned to tender codes.\\line 3) other things are optional.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 2007-08-06: }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f39\\fs20\\cf1\\insrsid10500608 Closed 83 as duplicate.\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 2007-08-08{\\*\\bkmkstart bugnotes}:}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608\\charrsid10500608  }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 The group decided to create a new issue \r\n{\\*\\bkmkend bugnotes}}{\\field{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608  HYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000223\" \\\\o \"[assigned] [Refactor] Adopt new tender codes (single set) and add circu\r\nit code to PJR\" }}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\f39\\fs20\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid10500608 CR223}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid10500608 \r\n to handle the basic tender code revision requirement.  This requirement, with data fields proposed by Chevron, is under consideration and will be voted on after committee members actually give feedback.\r\n\\par 2007-08-08: At a minimum, tender configuration is not required, i.e. the mapping from Circuitcode + whatever to a TenderCode is totally up to the POS to achieve without configuration from the BOS.\r\n\\par 2008-01-22: Final resolution - we will create a simple dataset allowing mapping circuit codes to NAXML tender codes. However this use is optional -- the POS may make the mapping decision without input.\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9111078 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000195\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid10492109\\charrsid10492109 CR195}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\r\n\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078  - [New Data] Add Coupon Maintenance and review journal treatment}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \r\n\\insrsid10492109\\charrsid9111078 \r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078 Description: Add maintenance functions for Coupons and review their treatment in the Journal.\r\n\\par Business Case: Essentially the committee recognizes that there are two types of coupons -- those that can be used as tenders and those that act as discounts. We\'ll have to disentangle those issues.  This feature is owned by the following TF:\\line \r\nDave Egan\\line Gregg Peele\\line Lisa Hester\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\ul\\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 Notes\r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 2007-08-07: The group decided that more research is needed, using the document\\line }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/node/781/\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 http://cms.pcats.org/node/781/}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\r\n\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078  as a starting place.\\line \\line Other issues:\\line Taxable vs. tax exempt\\line Tender vs. non-tender\\line Store vs. Manufacturer coupons\\line Scanning\r\n\\par 2008-04-25: Issues surrounding coupon processing in the convenience store include:\\line \\line General description of the process of coupon redemption plus...\\line \\line 1. How are coupons generally handled from an accounting perspective.\\line \r\n2. What identifiers are on coupons and how are these interpreted by the POS.\\line 3. What are the different types of coupons and the differences associated with each type.\\line 4. How are coupons associated with particular products?\\line \r\n5. What controls need to be in place to manage the type of coupons accepted?\\line 6. How are coupon doubling/tripling handled?\\line 7. How are coupons typically redeemed by the retailer and \r\nwhat is required by manufacturers in order to properly redeem those coupons.\r\n\\par 2008-06-10: Answers to questions from Kelly Spaugh (Submitted by Gregg Peele)\\line \\line I have the answers to our follow up questions:\\line \\line 1. Does a Manufacturer ever double their coupons? Th\r\ne decision to double coupons is made by the store. This is usually a competitive response to attract customers from other retailers. Rules around the $ limit (ie. up to .50 or up to 1.00) are set by the store. Manufacturers only pay the face value of the \r\ncoupon plus .08 since it is the store\\rquote s decision to double. Sometimes you will see \\\'93Do Not Double\\\'94 on coupons. This is because stores have asked manufacturers to add this statement to coupons distributed typically in the store.\\line \\line \r\n2. Where do grocery stores g\r\net their family codes from? Does the coupon/pos validate that code and how are they updated if they change? Family codes are created by the manufacturer to group products together for validation at the point of sale. Stores can get family code lists direc\r\nt\r\nly from manufacturers. Coupons Inc. offers a family code service in which retailers can purchase a list. If family codes change or new ones are added the manufacturers distribute updates. It is up to the retailer if they want to validate purchases to the \r\ncoupon\\rquote s company prefix or the company prefix AND family code. Family code list have not historically been accurate/current so some retailer choose to only validate to the company prefix.\\line \\line \\line \r\n3. Are coupons taxable or non taxable? We are not sure of this answer but think if you check with the FMI (}{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://www.fmi.org/\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \r\n\\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 http://www.fmi.org/}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 ) and/or the PMA (}\r\n{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 HYPERLINK \"http://www.pmalink.org/\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 http://www.pmalink.org/}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\r\n\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078\\charrsid9111078 ) you might be able to find that answer.\r\n\\par 2008-08-11: My thoughts on coupons:\\line 1. Manafacturer coupons should be vaildated against the ticket so they will need to be scanned when possible.\\line \r\n2. Manafacturer Coupons are a cash like instrument since the manufacturer will pay for the redemption. They also have value at the store down the street.\\line \r\n3. Store coupons are probably better treated like a discount, but should require a journal entry for category profit reporting. Usually there is not an exchange of cash involved for the value of the coupon.\\line \r\n2008-08-25: If the coupon item type is supported\r\n in version 4, guidelines should be provided as to whether the retail price associated with a coupon type item should be negative or positive, and whether the \"negative item flag\" should be assumed to be true, or provided explicitly.\r\n\\par 2008-08-20: Need to add coupon to the item type enumeration in ItemMaintenance.\r\n\\par 2008-08-20: Manufacturer coupons and retailer coupons should be reported separately.\\line Generally, manufacturer coupons will be reported as a tender, while retailer coupons may be reported as either a \r\nreduction to sales or as a tender, depending on the retailer\'s business practice.\r\n\\par 2008-09-18: Send the following email to Alvin Fortson at the Pantry\\line \\line Coupons:\\line \\line Coupons are setup by the back office in the following ways:\\line \\line 1. As an item (The type of an item can be set to a coupon.)\\line \r\n2. As a family code set at the item level. Family codes are sent to the POS along with the items sent. When the coupon is scanned, the manufacturer code of the item is compared with the manufacturer code and the family code on the\r\n coupon is compared with the family code on the item. If there is a match, the coupon is accepted.\\line \r\n3. If the coupon matches an item, the taxable nature of the coupon is designated by the taxable flags on the item. Otherwise, a setting on the POS must designate the taxable nature for coupons (usually based on the state.)\\line \r\n4. If the coupon matches an item, other information such as:\\line a. Whether the coupon is a % off or designates a particular value\\line b. Whether the coupon prompts for the value\\line c. Whether the coup\r\non automatically reduces the value (Cigarette Buy Down)\\line d. The number of times within a transaction the coupon can be used.\\line 5. The manufacturer code designates whether a coupon is a manufacturer coupon or a retail coupon\\line \r\n6. Manufacturer coupons are treated like tenders.\\line 7. Retailer coupons are treated like discounts or tenders depending on retailer business practices. (How does the Pantry handle this?)\\line \r\n8. If tenders are used exclusively, there are two tenders assumed, manufacturer and retail tenders as buckets for theses coupons.\r\n\\par }\\pard \\ltrpar\\ql \\li0\\ri0\\sa200\\sl276\\slmult1\\widctlpar\\wrapdefault\\aspalpha\\aspnum\\faauto\\adjustright\\rin0\\lin0\\itap0\\pararsid9514677 {\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000223\"}}{\\fldrslt {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\cs18\\ul\\cf20\\insrsid1978834\\charrsid1978834 CR223}}}\\sectd \\ltrsect\r\n\\linex0\\endnhere\\sectlinegrid360\\sectdefaultcl\\sectrsid7893941\\sftnbj {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid9111078  - }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f39\\fs20\\cf1\\insrsid9111078 \r\n[Refactor] Adopt new tender codes (single set) and add circuit code to PJR}{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f39\\fs20\\cf1\\insrsid1978834 \r\n\\par }{\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507\\afs20 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\f39\\fs20\\cf1\\insrsid9111078 Description: This issue is related to }{\\field\\fldedit{\\*\\fldinst {\\rtlch\\fcs1 \\af31507 \\ltrch\\fcs0 \\insrsid12852511 \r\nHYPERLINK \"http://cms.pcats.org/requests/bug_view_page.php?bug_id=0000188\" \\\\o \"[assigned] [New Data] Create Tender Configuratio