INSERT INTO `mantis_bug_text_table` VALUES (1,'Some convention is required for the content of required elements that are unsupported by the system producing a NAXML document, such as zeros for numeric elements and null for text elements.','',''),(2,'PaymentSystemsProductCode only accepts values in the range 001 thru 965.  This pre-supposes that all products MUST have a payment systems product code, even in environments where they are not used.  A value of zeros should be allowed, denoting the absence of a payment systems product code.','',''),(3,'I believe I submitted a request for version 3.3 to include a name attribute for POSCodeModifier.  That attribute is not presently provided.  At present, there is no other way to communicate the natural name of a retail package, short of appending it to the item description.\r\n\r\n<POSCodeModifier name=\"CARTON\">1</POSCodeModifier>','',''),(4,'NAXML-MovementReport/MerchandiseCodeMovement/MCMDetail/MCMSalesTotals/SalesAmount should have a value attribute indicating whether the amount the element contains is gross or net of voids, refunds, promotions, and discounts.','',''),(5,'Add prohibitEBT as an available enumeration for salesRestrictCodeBase','','EBT and food stamps, while equivalent in purpose in most states, are allowed or probibited independently of each other in some POS systems.'),(6,'WeekdayAvailability is configured as optional and non-repeatable in CBTDetail and MMTDetail. It should be repeatable.','','Unable to indicate whether a given promotion is available on more than one day of the week.  '),(7,'The use of AuthorizedChangeAmount in the DTD and AuthorizedChargeAmount.  The correct element name is AuthorizedChargeAmount.','',''),(9,'The element name State in the DTD is named StateOrProvince in the XSD.  StateOrProvince is the preferred name.','',''),(8,'The definition of SalesQuantity in the Version 3.3 DTD and XSD was identified.  SalesQuantity is defined with an attribute of UOMBasis in the DTD and uom in the XSD.  The group voted to change the DTD to conform to the schema.','',''),(10,'The presence of a required element named F in ItemLine in the POSJournal DTD.  Shouldn\'t be there - remove.','',''),(11,'The definition of the content of the Promotion element is not the same in the DTD and the XSD.  Change dtd to conform to the XSD.','',''),(12,'The use of  SalesRestrictCode and SalesRestriction is too permissive, defined as follows:\r\n(SalesRestrictCode | SalesRestriction*)* in each element within which the two are used.  This structure permits and unlimited number of SalesRestrictCode and SalesRestriction elements to occur in any order.  Change the definition of the choice to (SalesRestrictCode | SalesRestriction)?\r\n','',''),(13,'The values for the POSCodeFormat format attribute are all uppercase in the DTD and camelback case in the XSD.  Change dtd to match the XSD. ','',' Mr. Hervey noted that acronyms such as GTIN should probably be all uppercase in version 4.0'),(14,'Create a MovementReportRequest document format permitting a back office system to request movement reports for a specified reporting period from the POS.\r\n\r\nHere is a sample of the sort of data required:\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\r\n<DATAREREQUESTV320>\r\n  <TRANSHEADER>\r\n    <TRANSID>9999</TRANSID>\r\n    <TRANSDESCRIPTION>DAY request</TRANSDESCRIPTION>\r\n    <UPDATECODE>Urgent</UPDATECODE>\r\n    <GENERATIONDATE>16:06</GENERATIONDATE>\r\n    <GENERATIONTIME>19990519</GENERATIONTIME>\r\n    <SCHEMAVERSION>NAXML</SCHEMAVERSION>\r\n    <TESTFLAG>F</TESTFLAG>\r\n    <VENDORNAME>XXX</VENDORNAME>\r\n    <VENDORPRODUCTVERSION>Vendor XXX1.0</VENDORPRODUCTVERSION>\r\n  </TRANSHEADER>\r\n  <DETAIL>\r\n    <PERIOD>1</PERIOD>\r\n    <SUBPERIOD>0</SUBPERIOD>\r\n  </DETAIL>\r\n</DATAREREQUESTV320>','','This document format would allow retrieval of data previously exported in cases where it has been lost.'),(15,'test','',''),(16,'Create a transmission summary document format for NAXML to allow the sending system to provide a list of NAXML document files associated with a single transmission cycle.  The transmission summary can then act in two ways, first as a semaphore to the receiving system that the transmission is complete, and secondly as a manifest listing the document files that must be processed to insure that all files associated with the transmission cycle are processed at the same time.\r\n\r\nHere is a suggestion for content...\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n  <manifest source=\"PDI\" source_number=\"2004-03-25T16:48:25\">   \r\n  <file schema=\"x-schema:NAXMLv3.3_ITT\" name=\"ITT3.320040325114825.xml\" />\r\n  <file schema=\"x-schema:NAXMLv3.3_ILT\" name=\"ITL3.320040325114825.xml\" />\r\n</manifest>\r\n','','The transmission summary can then act in two ways, first as a semaphore to the receiving system that the transmission is complete, and secondly as a manifest listing the document files that must be processed to insure that all files associated with the transmission cycle are processed at the same time.'),(182,'In PBIBaseTypes, for miscellaneousSummarySubCodeBase, there is an enumeration that is listed twice in a row: “cardReaderCashAcceptor”.  Perhaps these are supposed to be two separate enumerations of “cardReader” and “cashAcceptor”?','',''),(183,'I found another enumeration that is not consistent.  In PBIBaseTypes, for posCodeFormatBase one of the enumerations is “plu”.  This is correct. However, in PBIDictionary, the “method” attribute of “EntryMethod” has an enumeration of “PLU”. Shouldn’t this be lowercase like all other enumerations?','',''),(184,'Is there a reason why SellingUnits is not required in ItemLine and ItemExemptionDetail, but IS required in ComponentItem?','',''),(185,'The enumerations for transactionTotalAmt attribute \"direction\" are currently \"Collected\" and \"Refunded\". These need to be lower case for consistency with all other enumerations.','',''),(186,'Add Local Account Maintenance\r\n\r\nThis feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDave Egan\r\nGregg Peele\r\nLisa Hester','','	<LocalAccountMaintenance>\r\n		<PrintStoreCopyOfReceipt>0</PrintStoreCopyOfReceipt>\r\n		<LocalAccountMaintenanceDetail>\r\n			<LocalAccountID>1</LocalAccountID>\r\n			<VatCode/>\r\n			<AccountName>Lisa&apos;s Store</AccountName>\r\n			<StreetAddress>1204 First Street</StreetAddress>\r\n			<City>Some City</City>\r\n			<State>Some State</State>\r\n			<ZipCode>99999</ZipCode>\r\n			<Country>Some Country</Country>\r\n			<PhoneNumber>999-999-9999</PhoneNumber>\r\n			<EmailAddress>emailme@test.com</EmailAddress>\r\n			<PrintCurrentBalanceOnCustReceipt>1</PrintCurrentBalanceOnCustReceipt>\r\n			<FixedAmount>1000</FixedAmount>\r\n			<HoldLimit>1000</HoldLimit>\r\n			<WarningLimit>999</WarningLimit>\r\n			<FloorLimit>1000</FloorLimit>\r\n			<SubAccountDetails>\r\n				<SubAccountID>00000000001</SubAccountID>\r\n				<SubAccountName>SubAccount 1</SubAccountName>\r\n				<VehicleIdentificationNo>23</VehicleIdentificationNo>\r\n				<SubAccountEnabled>1</SubAccountEnabled>\r\n			</SubAccountDetails>\r\n			<SubAccountDetails>\r\n				<SubAccountID>00000000002</SubAccountID>\r\n				<SubAccountName>SubAccount2</SubAccountName>\r\n				<VehicleIdentificationNo>5555</VehicleIdentificationNo>\r\n				<SubAccountEnabled>1</SubAccountEnabled>\r\n			</SubAccountDetails>\r\n		</LocalAccountMaintenanceDetail>\r\n	</LocalAccountMaintenance>\r\n\r\n'),(24,'Create a NAXML-SiteTraits document structure.','','To allow the exchange of site characteristics between trading partners.\r\n\r\nThis feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nTom Neumayer\r\nRaymond Lugo\r\nPaul Kern'),(25,'This is under CreditCardsPreDraft element.  Possible values are NoticeNumber and/or DocumentNumber or EFTNumber.','','Current version does not set a standard.  Value is arbitrary.'),(26,'The Account element is under the CreditCardsProcessed element.  Possible value is Location.','','Current version does not specify a standard value.  Value of attribute has to be agreed to with each trading partner.  '),(27,'This identType attribute should have the standard enumeration for an amount element (Debit, Credit)','','Currently this amount field must include a sign.  Should be handled the same as other amount elements.'),(28,'Suggest values of Automated and Manual.','','Standard values needed otherwise could be different for each trading partner.'),(29,'Needs to be configured as standard amount element.  Enumeration of Debit,Credit.','','Adding this attribute will make it more clear on how this element is supposed to be used.'),(30,'The example I have seen show identType attribute values of Proprietary and Non-proprietary, but there is not an enumeration on this attribute.  I am proprosing the values of BankCard and DebitCard be allowed.\r\n\r\nThere are also 2 amount attributes on this element, but no way to identify them as debits or credits without using a sign.  Maybe documentation would be enough to explain the usage of theis element.','','Need clarification to allow standard usage between multiple trading partners.'),(31,'Below is a snippet of xml for a charge for debit card fees.\r\nI wonder if the ChargeAmt element should be treated as a standard amount element and have the attributes of amount and identType?\r\n<CardType grossAmount=\"601.33\" identType=\"DebitCard\" netAmount=\"595.32\" quantity=\"29\">\r\n  <AllowanceOrCharge>\r\n    <AllowanceOrChargeReason>DebitCardFee</AllowanceOrChargeReason>\r\n    <ChargeAmt>-6.01</ChargeAmt>\r\n  </AllowanceOrCharge>\r\n</CardType>\r\n','','Standard needed.'),(32,'This should be treated as a standard amount element and have the attribute values of Credit, Debit.','','Needed for standard implementation.'),(33,'This element contains 3 amount attributes.  Should signs be used on the amounts or should an attribute be added to identify Debit or Credit?  Would all 3 amounts always be all positive or all negative?','','Clarification needed for standard implementation.'),(34,'EmployeeInformationMaintenance element was defined, but was left out of Maintenance document.  Would like it added back in.','','To enable employee time tracking capability at POS'),(35,'In SaleEvent, VoidEvent, and RefundEvent,VoidEvent, FinancialEvent, and OtherEvent the TillId element is required.  We do not believe it should be.','','Not all POS systems have multiple Tills, so this is not applicable.'),(36,'In PumpTestDetail currently PumpTestReason and PumpTesterID are required.  Would like these changed to optional','','Not all POS\'s have the ability to enter these values.'),(37,'The Tender element has TenderSubCode as a required sub element.  Would like it made optional.','','Not all POS support this concept.'),(38,'EnvelopeID and DropNumber  are currently required elements in SafeDropDetail.  Would like them made optional.','','Not all POS systems support these values.'),(39,'Add the following enumerations to punchReason.\r\nclockIn,clockOut','','To track clock in and clock out of employees at POS'),(40,'Would like the following subelements changed from required to optional in TimeClockDetail.\r\nDeviceID \r\nTaskID\r\nEntryMethod','','Not all POS systems provide this level of data'),(41,'Add prohibitTender to the nax:SalesRestrictCodeBase enumerations and, if necessary, open the content model for ITTData/SalesRestriction/SalesRestrictFlag to permit a tender ID to be transmitted in the element content.','','To allow a back office system to indicate that a given item may not be sold using one or more specified tenders. '),(42,'After submitting POS journal samples to the compliance testing tool, we found that it requires a namespace declaration in order to pass.  We are not sure that this should really be required in the instance documents.','',''),(43,'The current format of reporting Tenders as a sub report of the individual movement reports such as Item Sales, Mdse Sales, Fuel Sales, Combo Sales, etc... is not useable. The POS must allow for split tendered sales. \r\nThere needs to be a Tender Summary Movement report to report Tenders without forcing (illogical and/or unknown) associations to each item type sold. \r\nIf this reporting is placed in the Miscellaneous movement report, the ability to use tender sub codes as part of the reporting is lost.  ','','Tender reporting is a necessary part of POS/BO communication and there needs to be a standard way to deal with this issue instead of allowing every POS/BO vendor to add extensions to NAXML.'),(44,'There is currently no way to report Batch closes that go along with the transactions for the day.  This information is needed in order to reconcile terminal network totals to network deposits. This information is sent to the Back Office in order to accommodate this reconciliation process or to forward to a home office that will provide this function. This proposed change will allow for specifying batch level detail or shift/daily detail, in the event the payment host does not utilize batches. This proposed change will also allow for multiple batches per host or hosts if the POS can support multiple payment hosts. This data is common to POS/BO communication and a standard should be defined instead of allowing each POS/BO vendor to add extensions for this support. \r\n','',''),(45,'In the current schema there are seperate elements for a sale evebt, a void even, and a refund event.  Because these events typically have the same data, there seems to be an opportunity to simply the schema.','',''),(46,'Change the discount element in the ItemLine to allow mulltiple occurences instead of just 1.','','It is possiblt for an item to have multiple discounts applied to it at the item level.'),(47,'Currently schema only allows single discount element per fuelline.  Should change this to allow multiple occurences per fuel line.','','Can have multiple discounts applied to a fuel sale.'),(48,'Running a test case through the conformance tool, it returned saying that TransactionTotalGrandAmount was not defined in NAXMl dictionary, but looking at the dictionary it does appear to be defined.  Not sure where the poblem is.','',''),(49,'The RequestForMaintenance will permit a system to query another system to ask for a MaintenanceRequest document. This could be done by expanding the enumerations for TableAction to include \"read\" or \"request\".','','This can be used by a back office system to query a POS for its merchandise codes, fuel grades, etc.  It can likewise be used by a POS to request a maintenance document from the back office.  This may may be required in cases where the merchandise codes are maintained on the POS, but the back office needs the list of merchandise codes in order in insure that items transmitted by the back office are associated to valid merchandise codes.  Another use case would be when a newly staged POS is plugged into the store network and wants to request a pricebook and other configuration data from the back office.'),(50,'Modify FGTDetail to allow PaymentSystemsProductCode as an optional child of FGTData.','','Some credit networks use a unique product code for each product and service level.'),(51,'The usage of MovementHeader and SalesMovementHeader and their contents in MovementReport and POSJournal are somewhat ambiguous and confusing.  Rework them for the sake of clarity.','',''),(52,'Add a \"pointRelease\" attribute to NAXML-MaintenanceRequest.','','There is a need to denote the specific NAXML point release a given document is associated with.  The version attribute of the NAXML-MaintenanceRequest does not include the point release.'),(53,'Add some attributes or elements that allow a document provider to indicate that a document of a specific release also contains extensions in the extension points provided.','','Alerts the consumer to be ready for the presence of vendor extensions.  Submitted on behalf of David Godwin @ VeriFone.'),(55,'\"Include\" the NAMXL-StatesProvinces.xsd','','To be consistent with all other documents.'),(56,'\"Include\" the NAMXL-StatesProvinces.xsd','','To be consistent with all other documents.'),(57,'\"Include\" the NAMXL-StatesProvinces.xsd','','To be consistent with all other documents.'),(58,'\"Include\" the NAMXL-StatesProvinces.xsd','','To be consistent with all other documents.'),(59,'\"Include\" the NAMXL-StatesProvinces.xsd','','To be consistent with all other documents.'),(60,'\"Include\" the NAMXL-StatesProvinces.xsd','','To be consistent with all other documents.'),(61,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(62,'Minutes of August 17, 2004. ','',''),(63,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(64,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(65,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(66,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(67,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(68,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.  ','','PIDX version 2 only provides for one load date/time, and it\'s usage as start date/time or end date/time is mutually agreed upon between exhange partners.  Annotate elemetns to indicate that in such a case, that date/time should be loaded into the start and end date/time elements.'),(69,'Minutes of August 17, 2004','',''),(70,'Minutes of August 17, 2004.','',''),(71,'Would like to add a No Sale child financial event','','need to capture time date stamp on each \"no sale\" cash drawer event along with casher id.  Later in 4.0 would also like enumerated reason code.  Important data for fraud'),(72,'Add a device ID for Money Orders Devices for locations that may have multiple Money Orders.  The ID can be from 2 to 4 characters defined by the manufacturer. ','','All devices should have an ID for control of the device, reports or totals from a device.  '),(73,'May not be able to calculate a combo price when setting up a combo!  ','','I THINK THIS IS A BUG: Given that item lists can contain items of differing price we can\'t always deterministically calculate the discount price when we don\'t know what items from the item list trigger the combo.'),(74,'In 3.3.3 ComboItemList (part of CBTDetail) was changed to have a choice of  ComboItemUnitPrice or ComboItemDiscountAllocation.  In 3.3.2 this was not a choice, both elements were required.  In 3.3.4, this is again like it was in 3.3.2, both elements are required.  Would like it changed back to the way it was in 3.3.3, I do not believe it was supposed to be changed in 3.3.4\r\n ','',''),(75,'Backward compatibility of ComboMaintenance Broken!!!!!!!!!!!!  No % allocation in ComboItemList','','Against our rules!  broken backward compatibility!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!'),(76,'ComboItemList has both ComboItemUnitPrice and ComboItemDiscountAllocation as required elements.  A choice of one or the other should be required, but they should be mutually exclusive.','','If an overall combo price is specified, the POS is required to determine the resulting discount from the sum of the regular prices of the components minus the combo price.  Given this overall discount amount, then ComboItemDiscountAllocation should be used to indicate how much of the resulting discount should be allocated to the items from each item list.\r\n\r\nHowever, in some cases, a combo is constructed by specifying a discount or price for the items from each item list, on the assumption that the overall total price may vary, but the end result is a specific price or discount applied to one or more of the components (buy this item and get that item free, or buy this item and get that item for half price).'),(77,'add the enumeration tenderTypeDiscount to discountReasonBase in the PBIBaseTypes as part of 3.3.4','','It is common to offer a discount on certain things for using a prefered tender type.'),(78,'The MerchandiseCode should be optional for the FuelGradeMaintenance and the ItemMaintenance nodes.','','When doing a pricing only download we only know the price information for that item and not the MerchandiseCode.  The POS does not necessarily need this information.'),(79,'In ComboMaintenance the ComboUnitPrice should not be required.  The ComboUnitPrice as well as the ComboPrice (CR #73) are not known until the time of the sale.  The BOS does not have this information...only the discount information.','',''),(80,'BUG - Nax:number8 is limited to nonNegitive integers of 16 digits should be 8 digits','',''),(81,'Transaction Total Gross Amount has the following documentation note:\r\nThe gross amount of the transaction before applying transaction level discounts, promotions, taxes, etc.\r\n\r\nDoes this mean that this total should include Item level discounts, promotions etc?  Just want to make sure I am clear on what I should be providing here.','',''),(82,'TransactionLine has an attribute type, with one of the enumerations being return.  The documentation annotation reads \"Normal indicates anormally completed, unmodified transaction line. Cancel indicates a transaction line that was rung and then reversed, and is therfore not included in the transation total and does not impact store inventory. Return indicate a transaction line for a product returned by the customer for credit as part of a sale transaction. Refund transactions would not use this status.  This status could also be used to record foodservice orders that were cancelled after the order was prepared.  Return aquantity is assumed to be a positive number.  Retun is not applicable to Tender, PromotionTrigger, PromotionReward, TransactionTax, or CustomerID transaction lines. Other indicates transaction line whose status is user-defined and qulified by the element TransactionLineStatusDescription\"  What if in a transaction that has non-taxed sales, there is a taxed item that is returned.  How do you denote the tax amount that is being given back to the customer?  What is the reason for saying TransactionTax can not be a type of return.','','A customer buys fuel (non-taxed sale), and returns a dry item in the same sale.  The Total transaction has a positive sales vaule, so it is not a refund transaction, yet the total transaction tax amount is in effect negative.  This is shown iin the attached file.'),(83,'Add a content model permitting the transmission of tenders to and from the POS.','',''),(84,'Would like to add nax:extension group to Maintenance in first sequence that contains maintenance document categories.','','We need to be able to maintain \"Local Accounts\" at the BOS.  Would like this to be accomplished with a NAXML extension rather than having to have our own seperate scheme for this function.  Will propose our solution later as a NAXML 4.0 enhancement'),(85,'Submitting the following product code insertions to the codes reserved for NACS Future Use:\r\nNACS Code        Product Description\r\n045                    B2 Diesel Blend 2% Biodiesel\r\n046                    B5 Diesel Blend 5% Biodiesel\r\n047                    B10 Diesel Blend 10% Biodiesel\r\n048                    B20 Diesel Blend 20% Biodiesel\r\n049                    B100 Diesel Blend 100% Biodiesel\r\n','','July 1, 2005, all gas stations that sell diesel in Minnesota MUST (by state mandate) turn over to bio-diesel. (B2 is replacing all DSL)\r\n\r\nJuly 2006 Federal mandate for ultra-low sulfur diesel which \r\nwil be different bio-blends.\r\n\r\nIdaho has B20 Requirement'),(86,'Would like to add nax:extension group to Movement in first sequence that contains movement document categories. (Similar to Harry Parham\'s request for the Maintenance schema)','','Need for an extension element whereby new report sections could be added to NAXML Movement.  '),(87,'Both TillID and DropNumber were made optional in 3.3.4 and are  still required for safe drop journal cert test.','','Both were specifically made optional for this use case.'),(88,'Some POS systems allow to create refunds on financial events (e.g. cashier performed a safe drop of $20,00 but made a mistake, and entered only $10.00 at the POS, so he can create a safe drop refund on $10.00 and perform correct safe drop of $20.00).\r\n\r\nTherefore the extension of the \"status\" attribute\'s enumerator is needed, in order for the POS to export such a case (the only available values of the enumerator \'status\' today are \"normal\", \"cancel\" and \"void\").','',''),(89,'The use case used by the conformance test tool for a void and a refund transaction require the following optional elements:\r\nTransactionLineStatusDescription\r\nInventoryItemId\r\nRoundingAmount\r\nThese elements are not required for the sales transaction use cases.','','Sales uses case and the refund/void use case should be similiar in the optional elements required.  TransactionLineStatusDescription, InventoryItemId, and RoundingAmount are not used by all POS vendors and should not be required to pass the conformance test.'),(90,'In 3.3x there is no maintenece record to set up tenders.  Would like to add this in 4.0','','Tenders are being reported as part of sales data coming out of the POS.  To ensure the correct tender identifiers are being used, the BOS should be able to send tender information to the POS.'),(91,'TransactionTotalGrandAmount and TransactionTotalNetAmount have the same definition in the schema.  This amgibuity must be resolved.','',''),(92,'All quantity and amount values should be defined in such a way as to achieve a consistent use of negative and positive values so as to result in an accurate representation of goods and currency entering or leaving the store.','',''),(93,'In cases where the financial or inventory impact of a given transaction must be reversed because the original transaction was in error, a consistent mechanism for doing so is needed.','','See POS/BOS 3.3 change request #88'),(94,'Since the fixed attribute of version number prevents backward compatability anyway, let\'s change it so that it\'s not fixed, or have a major version attribute that is fixed and make the minor version an attribute that is not fixed.\r\n\r\nOther alternatives would be make it an element.\r\n','','With this attribute, it makes it impossible to validate an eariler instance document with a later minor version of the schema.\r\n'),(95,'Request that the datatype restriction to \"integer\" be changed to \"string\"','','Suppliers often use alpha-numeric and hyphens (-) as part of their invoice numbers.'),(96,'Two GradeMaintenance use cases are classified as core use cases, and I feel they should not be. The use cases in question are:\r\n\r\nGrade Maintenance - Price Change by Price Tier & Position - Add/Change \r\n\r\nGrade Maintenance - Price Change by Price Tier & Position - Intialize \r\n\r\nHowever, not all vendors send Grade Maintenance information (pricing and blending) on a position-by-position basis. These use cases should be classified as non-CORE. \r\n','','Some POS Vendors configure the grade information (blending and pricing) independently from the assignment of the grades to a fueling position. These vendors would not have position information in the GradeMaintenance documents, as it has no meaning.\r\n\r\n'),(97,'Add ordinal attribute to FuelLine, FuelPrepayLine, ItemLine, TenderInfo, & WashCodeLine to indicate positional order on receipt.\r\n','','We need a place to store ordinals for various items to keep track of their order within a ticket, as it cannot always be assumed that the order in the XML document is the order in the ticket/receipt.\r\n \r\nFuelLine, FuelPrepayLine, ItemLine, TenderInfo, and WashCodeLine should each have an attribute to store the ordinal (an integer).\r\n \r\nI understand that TransactionLine/TransactionLineSequenceNumber and SubItemLine/SubItemLineSequenceNumber are intended for the purpose of ordinals, but in order to have an ordinal for each item, they couldn\'t be put under one TransactionLine, which is the intended design of the schema. Each ItemLine, FuelLine, WashCodeLine, and TenderInfo would have to have their own TransactionLine, so you end up with many TransactionLines, all with only one main child element.'),(98,'We have not found anything in the current schema for handling check cashing. Please correct me if I am wrong about this. Could a child element be added to FinancialEventDetail for this information?','',''),(99,'I have not found any useful documentation or examples of user-defined extensions. I\'m not clear on how extensions work and how exactly they are implemented. I see where the defined extension points are at in the schema, but I don\'t know what to do from there.','',''),(100,'Create a document structure allowing requests for movement reports','','Need a document structure that permits the back office system to request a set of movement reports from the POS for a specified business date.'),(101,'Currently, simpleType nax:batchTypeBase (which, I guess is actually defined in NAXML-PBIBaseTypes33.xsd) has enumeration of \"credit\" and \"debit\" only. We would like \"moneyOrder\" to be added to this list. This would be for use in the BatchDetail/BatchType element of POSJournal. \r\n\r\nI put this request under DataDictionary, even though it is actually the PBIBaseTypes file that would need to be modified. Hopefully this was the correct way of doing this request.','',''),(102,'Modify the content model for TransactionLimit to permit the expression of transaction limits in terms of currency instead of or in addition to quantity.','','Money orders in particular are often subjected to a limit on both the number of money orders that may be sold to an individual and/or the total value of the money orders that may be sold to an individual, primarily to avoid the  reporting burdens imposed by federal regulations'),(105,'Attribute is defined as type nax:description8.  Need it increased in length to a minimum of 10.','','Must truncate retail package descriptions to fit in 8 characters.'),(106,'Create IXRetail_CurrencyCodes.xsd','',''),(107,'Create PCATS-BaseTypes.xsd','',''),(104,'Modify SalesRestriction to permit the inclusion of tender restrictions','','At present there is no means by which one or more specific tenders can be prohibited for use with a given item if SalesRestriction is used instead of SalesRestrictCode.\r\n'),(108,'Create PCATS-EnumCountryCodes.xsd','',''),(109,'Create PCATS-EnumLanguages.xsd','',''),(110,'Create PCATS-EnumStatesProvinces.xsd','',''),(111,'Create PCATS-EnumUOM.xsd','',''),(112,'Create PCATS-Foundation.xsd','',''),(113,'Create URL http://www.pcats.org/Schema/PCATS-Foundation','',''),(114,'Create URL http://www.pcats.org/Schema/PCATS-Foundation/V1.0','',''),(115,'Create URL http://www.pcats.org/Docs/PCATS-Foundation/V1.0','',''),(116,'Create URL http://www.pcats.org/Docs/PCATS-Foundation','',''),(117,'Promotion Setup:\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nA customer purchasing any 330ml soft drink with any 10oz chips he will get a 10% discount.\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSale Scenarios\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1. The customer purchased qty 1 of 300ml Coke and qty 1 10oz bar-b-q chips. Received a 10% discount. \r\n2. The customer purchased qty 2 of 300ml Coke and qty 2 10oz bar-b-q chips. Received a 10% discount. \r\n3. The customer purchased qty 1 of 300ml Coke, qty 1 of 10oz bar-b-q chips, qty 1 of regular chips and qty 1 of 300ml Pepsi. Received a 10% discount. \r\n \r\n\r\nCurrent NAXML Reporting\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1. The qty of 1 coke was sold with a promotion of 10% and the qty of 1 10oz bar-b-q chips was sold with a promotion of 10% \r\n2. The qty of 2 coke was sold with a promotion of 10% and the qty of 2 10oz bar-b-q chips was sold with a promotion of 10% \r\n3. The qty of 1 coke was sold with a promotion of 10%, the qty of 1 10oz bar-b-q chips, the qty of 1 10oz regular chips were sold with a promotion of 10% and the qty of 1 Pepsi was sold with a promotion of 10%. \r\n \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIssues\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSale Scenarios\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n1. Scenario 1: No issue, the BOS has enough information to establish that 1 promotion was triggered with the correct amount. \r\n2. Scenario 2: How many times was the promotion triggered? This is open for interpretation. Some will say the promotion was triggered twice and some will say that the promotion was trigger only once even with the qty of 2. When interfacing between POS and BOS it is important that both systems should the same values. \r\n3. Scenario 3:What was the item combination that triggered the promotion?  Was it the Pepsi and the regular chips the coke and the bar-b-q chips or was it the Pepsi and the bar-b-q chips the Coke and the regular chips? This information is needed to better analyze the promotion result and to establish pattern for future promotions etc. etc. \r\n \r\n\r\nSolution\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nTo add a new element either under transaction detail or under transaction summary called Promotion Line that will have the details of each promotion and what triggered the promotion\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nSale Scenarios\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\nIt will show once that promotion was triggered and 2 sub lines with the coke information and the chips information. \r\nPending how the POS will report. \r\nfor POS’s reporting that the promotion was triggered once it will show once the promotion and 2 sub lines with the coke information (qty 2) and the chips information (qty 2). \r\nFor POS’s reporting that the promotion was triggered twice it show either \r\n                                                               i.      2 line for the promotion and 2 sub lines with the coke information (qty 1) and the chips information (qty 1).\r\n\r\n                                                             ii.      1 line for promotion with the qty of 2 and 2 sub lines with the coke information (qty 2) and the chips information (qty 2).\r\n\r\n2 lines for the promotion, each line will have 2 sub lines what is the combination that triggered this promotion. \r\n \r\n','','Allows tracking of promotions to establish the effectiveness of a particular promotion.'),(118,'We need a place to store the results of fuel meter readings, which apparently is different from a pump test. This is the structure we are looking for: \r\n\r\n<DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n	<Dispenser id=\'x\'>\r\n		<Reading type=\'x\'>\r\n			<Product id=\'x\'>\r\n				<Amount>00000000.000</Amount>\r\n			</Product>\r\n		</Reading>\r\n	</Dispenser>\r\n</DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n\r\nDispenser@id would be the FuelPositionID. \r\nReading@type would be, for us, one of three things: Sales Volume, Pure Volume, or Sales Amount. \r\nProduct@id would be the FuelGradeID. \r\nAmount would be a number with 8 positions and 3 decimal places.\r\n\r\nSo, there can be multiple dispensers with multiple readings (one of each type) with each reading type having multiple products, with only one amount per product.','','Need the ability to record meter readings received from an Allied box in the POSJournal any time the fuel pricing changes.'),(119,'The Void and Refund use cases for POSJournal require fields not required in the Sales Use cases.  These are:\r\n\r\nTransactionLineSequenceNumber\r\nTransactionTotalTaxExemptAmount \r\nTransactionTotalTaxForgivenAmount\r\nTaxExemptCertificateID\r\nTransactionTotalGrandAmount\r\n','','Refund and void transactions have the same basic business information requirements as a sales transaction.  Why would the use cases be different.  Also, some of the elements being required, would not apply in most cases.'),(120,'MMTDetail/WeekdayAvailability is optional, but not repeatable.','','Need to be able to repeat WeekdayAvailability for each day of the week if necessary.'),(121,'Right now there is only \'VehicleDescription\'. We save individual data such as vehicle color and vehicle type. Perhaps we could have color and type added as optional attributes for VehicleDescription. Or add additional optional child elements under DriveOffDetail for VehicleColor and VehicleType.\r\n\r\nI can add more detail about this later.','',''),(122,'The annotation for MixMatchDiscountAmount states \"The money amount discount to apply to this group\".  It is ambiguous with respect to whether the discount amount is the per unit amount to apply to each of the eligible units or whether the discount amount should be divided across the total number of eligible units.  Take the following example:\r\n<MixMatchEntry>\r\n  <MixMatchUnits>3</MixMatchUnits>\r\n  <MixMatchDiscountAmount>1.00</MixMatchDiscountAmount>\r\n</MixMatchEntry>\r\n\r\nDoes this mean that the POS should apply a $1.00 discount to each of the 3 units, or does it mean that the total of the discounts applied to each unit should be $1.00?','',''),(123,'This is in addition to the CR #118 which was for version 3.3.4. For version 4.0 it was suggested the possible use of a complex type as a basis for both FPMDetail and the new structure I am proposing.\r\n\r\nWe need a place to store the results of fuel meter readings.\r\n\r\nHere are the details of my original proposal:\r\n\r\nI have two different versions for you to consider.\r\n\r\nTotalAmount will be either in gallons or dollars, depending on the readingType. The units wouldn\'t need to be specified, as the readingType makes the units for TotalAmount implied.\r\n\r\nThis didn\'t really fit into a movement report. It\'s just an OtherEvent in POSJournal.\r\n\r\nXML Document Example:\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<OtherEvent>\r\n			<--Insert many required elements here-->\r\n			<DispenserMeterDetail readingType=\"Pure Volume\">\r\n				<FuelPositionID>1</FuelPositionID>\r\n				<FuelGradeID>1</FuelGradeID>\r\n				<TotalAmount>999.999</TotalAmount>\r\n			</DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n		</OtherEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n\r\n<nax:DispenserMeterDetail readingType=\"nax:description24 [1]\">\r\n<nax:FuelPositionID>  ... </nax:FuelPositionID> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeID> ... </nax:FuelGradeID> [1]\r\n<nax:TotalAmount> ... </nax:TotalAmount> [1]\r\nModel group reference (not shown): nax:extension [0..1]\r\n</nax:DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n\r\n<nax:TotalAmount> nax:decimalValue8 </nax:TotalAmount>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"DispenserMeterDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelPositionID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:TotalAmount\"/>\r\n<xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:attribute name=\"readingType\" type=\"nax:description24\" use=\"required\"/>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TotalAmount\" type=\"nax:decimalValue8\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAlternatively, it could be done this way (with FuelGradeSalesAmount holding the amount for reading type \'Sale Amount\',  FuelGradeSalesVolume holding the amount for reading type \'Sale Volume\', and FuelProductVolume holding the amount for  reading type \'Pure Volume\', eliminating the need for the reading type to be stored, as it is a choice between these  three amounts):\r\n\r\nXML Document Example:\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<OtherEvent>\r\n			<--Insert many required elements here-->\r\n			<DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n				<FuelPositionID>1</FuelPositionID>\r\n				<FuelGradeID>1</FuelGradeID>\r\n				<FuelGradeSalesVolume>999.999</FuelGradeSalesVolume>\r\n			</DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n		</OtherEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n\r\n<nax:DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n<nax:FuelPositionID>  ... </nax:FuelPositionID> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeID> ... </nax:FuelGradeID> [1]\r\nStart Choice [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount> ... </nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume> ... </nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelProductVolume> ... </nax:FuelProductVolume> [1]\r\nEnd Choice\r\nModel group reference (not shown): nax:extension [0..1]\r\n</nax:DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"DispenserMeterDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelPositionID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeID\"/>\r\n<xs:choice>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"FuelGradeSalesAmount\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"FuelGradeSalesVolume\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"FuelProductVolume\"/>\r\n</xs:choice>\r\n<xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n','',''),(124,'Change AuthorizingCashierID from nax:id4 to nax:id40 to be consistent with CashierID. Or at least extend it to a length greater than 4. I believe the longest we allow for is 9 in our current database. I don\'t see any reason why AuthorizingCashierID should be restricted to a length of 4.','',''),(125,'We plan on storing our shift sequence number, which allows for up to 12 digits, in PrimaryReportPeriod of JournalHeader. Currently nax:reportPeriod is a union of data and string of length 8. We would appreciate this being increased to length 12.','',''),(126,'The specification does not explicitly state whether check digits are to be used when sending item information.  A search of the minutes reveals that this has been discussed by the group on at least two occasions (as given below) but no action appears to have been taken.\r\n\r\nVerifone proposes that Mr. Wade\'s suggestion of March 12, 2004 be adopted (adding a new checkDigit attribute to the POSCodeFormat).  If the attribute is not present or is not checked, the behavior will be implementation-defined.\r\n\r\n[September 22, 1998] The task force concluded that there really was not a need for the check digit and suggested removing the requirement of having a check digit as part of the guidelines.\r\n\r\n[March 12, 2004] Mr. Hervey opened the meeting by showing some instance documents he created to implement the use cases identified the previous day.  Mr. Godwin observed that the UCC representative at the January meeting stated that all barcode numbers should be exchanged with the check digit included.  Ms. Byerley noted her belief that this is a UCC requirement (as opposed to a recommendation) for the GTIN.  Mr. Wade recommended that an attribute be added to POSCodeFormat to indicate whether the check digit is included.\r\n','','The two NACS demonstration sessions were both conducted without use of check digits; however, UCC has since recommended that check digits always be transferred whenever exchanging GTIN information (or its various subsets, such as UPC).  Confusion exists within the retailer and vender community as to the exact requirement.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n'),(127,'Somewhere in the last few revisions of the schema, the content model for the Location element was omitted.','','Lack of a content model prevents the identification of the location to which the invoice applies.'),(128,'Testing against the \"PBI Maintenance v3.3.4-2\" schema, I submitted an instance document for TankProductMaintenance. The instance document had all of the mandatory elements. I received an error from the conformance tool that stated more elements were expected. The elements listed are all optional.\r\n\r\nThis same instance document will pass conformance using the \"PBI Maintenance v3.3.3-2\" schema. \r\n\r\nAre we now going to require all of these elements for passing the use case? Or does the use case schema used by the tool need to be updated.\r\n\r\n\r\nBelow is the response from the conformance tool:\r\n-------------------------------------------\r\nSubmitted instance document is not valid against the nominated Use Case. \r\nXerces generated validation errors follow: \r\nLine:16 - cvc-complex-type.2.4.b: The content of element \'TankData\' is not complete. One of \'{\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankInstallDate, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankManifoldID, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankManufacturer, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankModelNumber, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankSerialNumber, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankDepth, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankLowInventoryVolume, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankReorderVolume, \"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\":TankVolume}\' is expected.\r\n-----------------------------------------------','','Not all of the information the conformance tool is claiming to require is available for all POS systems.'),(129,'Change DiscountReason to use of optional, add an additional optional element of DiscountDescription, and set it to be a choice between these two so that only one is required. This would require descriptive information about the discount to be entered without relying on the enumerated list of discount reasons. DiscountDescription would just be of type nax:id40.','','The way we have our discounts set up, each store can set up their own discounts with their own descriptions. They do not necessarily conform to anything in the current enumeration for DiscountReason and there is no real way to add everything that we might possibly need.'),(130,'MixMatchDiscount and MixMatchAmount are set up as a choice. It may be better to allow the discount to be reported as an optional element (and the DiscountPercent element as well) That way rounding issues can be avoided because you can report that actual cents off discount when funky mix-match setups are used.','','A mix-match for 4/$1.29 exists, strict low flag is false. Two items are sold. The mix match quantity is 4, the mix-match price is $1.29, what is the discount that was actually applied to the two items?'),(131,'For the use case \"Item List Maintenance - Initialize\" in the group \"Promotion/Combo Maintenance\" the tool is expecting the <MerchandiseCode> element in the <ItemListEntry> section.\r\n\r\nPart of the 3.3.4 changes were to make the <MerchandiseCode> optional. Having an <ItemListEntry> with <ItemCode> and <MerchandiseCode> is technically possible (schema compliant), but was not the intended usage for this document.','','The schema had an error where a sequnce had been used instead of a choice. A fix was made as part of 3.3.4 to make the elements of the sequence optional. Excerpt from the schema:\r\n\r\n\"Ideally, a choice of ItemCode, MerchandiseCode, or GroupCode should be used here.  The use of one or more of them is allowed to preserve backward compatibility with version 3.3.3\"'),(132,'Part of the 3.3.4 changes were to make the <MerchandiseCode> optional. Having an <ItemListEntry> with <ItemCode> and <MerchandiseCode> is technically possible (schema compliant), but was not the intended usage for this document.\r\n\r\nThe schema had an error where a sequnce had been used instead of a choice. A fix was made as part of 3.3.4 to make the elements of the sequence optional. Excerpt from the schema:\r\n\r\n\"Ideally, a choice of ItemCode, MerchandiseCode, or GroupCode should be used here. The use of one or more of them is allowed to preserve backward compatibility with version 3.3.3\" ','','A choice is a better model for the intended use of ItemLists'),(134,'The wording of the DiscountCount and PromotionCount elements uses the words \"number of transactions\".  Example of DiscountCount annotation is below:\r\nTotal number of discount transactions associated with the DiscountAmount for the item/merchandise code/fuel grade being reported.\r\n\r\nQuestion whether this should really be the count of discounts or promotions applied?  More than one discount or promotion may occur in a transaction.  Should the individual discounts and promotions applied be counted, or should it be counted as 1 transaction?','',''),(135,'Requesting the addition of an optional element \"Message ID\" at same level as tender request reference number.','','Using the CLT and CLTR requires two-way communication between the delivery scheduling system and the carrier dispatch system.  A single Truck Tender Request can have multiple requests and responses which may not happen sequentially. The message ID indicates which request a response is for.  '),(136,'Requesting the addition of an optional element \"Message ID\" at same level as tender request reference number.','','Using the CLT and CLTR requires two-way communication between the delivery scheduling system and the carrier dispatch system.  A single Truck Tender Request can have multiple requests and responses which may not happen sequentially. The message ID indicates which request a response is for.  '),(137,'Requesting the addition of an optional element \"Message ID\" at same level as tender request reference number.','','Using the CLT and CLTR requires two-way communication between the delivery scheduling system and the carrier dispatch system.  A single Truck Tender Request can have multiple requests and responses which may not happen sequentially. The message ID indicates which request a response is for.  '),(138,'Requesting an optional element Truck Tender Request Reference # at same level as invoice number on fuel freight invoice.','','This will allow matching a fuel freight invoice and delivery report to a load that was dispatched using the CLT'),(139,'Requesting the addition of optional shift start and end time to the truck tender request attributes.','','This will allow a user who schedules dedicated truck capacity in a delivery scheduling system to indicate to the receiveing carrier dispatch system which shift a load is scheduled for..'),(140,'This is more of a discussion item.  It seems like the RVP, RFG, OXY attributes may need to be optional.   Additionally, it would be valuable to understand how these attributes were envisioned to be used.','','I am not sure in all cases this information would be available. '),(141,'Would it be possible to provide values of 001, 002, 003 to indicate whether the shift is a day shift, night shift.  North America typically has 2 shifts.  European countries may have 3.  ','','This will help specify which shift of the day a load is being scheduled for.'),(142,'Would it be possible to conform on a equipment types within the truck tender request attribute equipType?  Recommended: Semi, SemiSleeper, TruckTrailer, Bobtail','','Help specify the type of truck that can delivery a load.'),(143,'Requesting that the types of \"ListOrder\" & \"DedicatedTruck\" be added as values for the CLT requestType attribute.  ','','This will allow a delivery scheduling system to indicate to the carrier dispatch system whether the truck tender requests in the CLT are list orders or for dedicated truck capacity.  Otherwise, not sure what value of requestType at the CLT level is when a requestType exists at the Truck Tender Request level.'),(144,'Requesting an optional field for truck restrictions at same level as customer instructions on the truck tender request','','This will allow the delivery scheduling system to indicate to the carrier dispatch system whether there ar special truck requirements at the site where the load is being delivered to.  For instance, is a pump required or is an offside fill hose required'),(145,'This is really a request for all documents.  Currently there is an identType attribute for most ID attributes.  There is no real definition for these. It seems the values of SenderID, ReceiverID, AgencyID, or IndustryID should be used.  SenderID indidcates to the receiver that the value belongs to the sender in the transmission header and it will likely need to be translated into the receiver\'s id.  ReceiverID indicates to the receiver that the value is their own and no translation is necessary. Agency ID indicates the the ID belongs to the transmission agency in the transmission header and the receiver will likely have to translate it into their own id.  Industry ID indicates that a mutually agreed upon industry standard is being used for the id values.  Example would be SCAC codes, PIDX codes, TCN Numbers, etc... ','','To provide conformity on ID types and to clarify which trading partner is the owner of the ID.  This will ease programming around translation procedures.'),(146,'Requesting an optional field Loading # instead of using release #.  This would be at the same level as release #.','','If the request is coming from a procurement system the release number may serve other purposes.  Adding the loading number would clarify what the value is and would provide for the event that both a requisition release number and loading number exist.'),(147,'Can we change miles to distance or add an optional attribute of distance?  This may require specifying the distance unit as well.','','Would like for the standard to support kilometers and miles.'),(148,'Requesting an optional element \"Delivery Number\" to be added to the DeliveryStop at the same level as PurchaseOrderNumber','','This will allow unique identifiers for deliveries and orders.  Likewise, if there are multiple deliveries for one order, this will allow differentiating betweent the deliveries.'),(149,'Please make BOL unbounded.','','Would like to send multiple BOLs in one Transportation envelope'),(150,'Requesting an optional field Loading # instead of using release #. This would be at the same level as release #. ','','This will allow clarification between a requistion release number and loading number.  It is true that the loading number on a BOL will generally be the release number from a vendor\'s perspective so this request is not critical, but we are seeking consistency with the previous request 146 which asks for a loading number on the CLT. It is more important for the CLT.'),(151,'Add optional invoice number element at the same level as bill of lading number on the BOL','','In the event that a supplier distributes a BOL after they have generated the invoice in their back office, it would be possible for them to attach the corresponding invoice number.  This would be valuable in matching BOLs to Invoices.  Some suppliers currently do this within their own BOL extranet solutions.'),(152,'Requesting an optional element added to the original transmission header in  the acknowledgement document to indicate the original file name.','','Some of our trading partners have requested that we return the file name... To support this, we are using a modified version of the pcat ACK'),(153,'Currently, TransactionID is type nax:id8. Our ticket numbers can be up to 12 digits long. The next highest type available would be nax:id16. We request that TransactionID (and OriginalTransactionID) be changed to nax:id16.','',''),(154,'NAXML needs to support UTF16','','This is a requirement for international use of the standard.'),(155,'The Maintenance document needs to support maintenance of multiple exchange rates by BOS.','','Many countries outside the US and Canada accept more than one currency.  We need to be able to manage the exchange rate through the interface.'),(156,'Country Code needs to be extended to contain all ANSI country codes.  Currently only contains US and Canada.','','This is required for use of NAXML in countries outside the US.'),(157,'Could be extended by adding a String to State or Province Base Union.  ','','Currently only Provinces in Canada and States in US are supported.  Need to support other countries if standard is to become international.'),(158,'Add support for maintenance of Discount Reason Code enumerator by BOS','','Discount reasons change more rapidly than configuration allows. The result is that we live with \"canned reasons\" that do not reflect real reason discount was given.'),(159,'Add support for Item quick key maintenance.','','Many POS\'s support changing Item quick key maintenance centrally.'),(160,'Add acknowledge document attached below to NAXML schema or some equal or better document','','We have had to extend NAXML to support reliable messaging.  Ack document has improved reliability of interface in our system in the Phillipines.'),(161,'Add support for maintenance of House Charge (local accounts) accounts to maintanence Doc.','','This is required to support management of local accounts by BOS'),(162,'Mix and Matches can be modeled by Combo maintenance.  They are a subset of Combo maintenance.  Why not do away with Mix and match.','','Simplify the schema!  Improve interoperability of complient POS\'s and Back Office Systems.'),(163,'Currently Fuels sales can be modeled using the item line and item type of fuel or more appropiately by the Fuel line in the journal.  Why have two ways to do the same thing.  Lets agree to utilize the most appropiate way which is the fuel line!','','Multiple POS and Back Office system interoperability will be enhanced if we can have one powerful method to report fuel sales!'),(164,'Add support for \"no sale\" event to journal that will log all entries to cash draws.  Event should pass time, cashier id, draw id, etc.','','Fraud Prevention '),(165,'In case of an aborted receipt, there are no transaction lines to be passed to the BOS, so VoidEvent won\'t work as it is.','',''),(166,'Similar to the SaleEvent\'s TransactionLine there should be RoundingAmount node for FinancialEvent\'s PayInDetail and PayOutDetail','',''),(167,'Many POS systems support local account prepayments (received on account) and deposit payments. There should be a possibility to export these data to the backoffice.','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDave Egan\r\nGregg Peele\r\nLisa Hester'),(168,'The details of FuelPrepayLine are insufficient for proper export of prepayment data, especially if there are discounts applied to the prepayment.','',''),(169,'The ComboItemQuantity in the ComboItemList needs to be changed to a choice \"ComboItemQuantity\" or \"ComboAmount\".','','A promotion like: Buy any goods for $ 50.00 and get 10% off.'),(170,'ComboItemDiscountAllocation\'s attribute type needs to be extended by the following values:\r\nno discount\r\ncheapest free\r\nfixed price\r\npercent pro-rata\r\namount pro-rata','','Support of promotions with all these kinds of discounts. \"Fixed price\" is also extra mentioned here, although there is ComboItemUnitPrice. Sometimes the sales amount is applied not to a unit of an item, but to a basket of items. E.g. \"Buy any 3 soft drinks for $2.00\".'),(171,'The TSTDetail structure permits only one TaxLevel to be associated to a TaxStrategy.\r\n\r\n<!--TaxStrategyMaintenance structures-->\r\n<xs:element name=\"TaxStrategyMaintenance\">\r\n   <xs:annotation>\r\n      <xs:documentation>\r\n         Tax Strategy Maintenance (TST) Contains those\r\n         data elements, which need to be sent from the BO\r\n         to the POS system to maintain methods and\r\n         algorithms for the application of tax to\r\n         items/merchandise code/fuel grade.\r\n      </xs:documentation>\r\n   </xs:annotation>\r\n   <xs:complexType>\r\n      <xs:sequence>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:TableAction\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:TSTDetail\" \r\n                     minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n      </xs:sequence>\r\n   </xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n<xs:element name=\"TSTDetail\">\r\n   <xs:complexType>\r\n      <xs:sequence>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyID\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelID\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelSequenceID\"\r\n                     minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyDescription\"\r\n                     minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n         <xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n      </xs:sequence>\r\n   </xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>','','Prevents the creation of a TaxStrategy that enables taxes for multiple tax levels.'),(172,'Had a question around Reason Codes for PayIn and PayOut transactions:\r\n\r\nWhen we were going through NAXML POS Journal certification we had to use hard coded reason codes for PayIn and PayOut transactions.\r\n\r\n<PayInReason>payInReason</PayInReason>\r\n<PayOutReason>payOutReason</PayOutReason>\r\n\r\nIs this still a requirement or was that just a constraint of the conformance tool.  Can we not use POS defined reason codes instead of the standard \"payInReason\" and \"payOutReason\" reason codes?\r\n','',''),(173,'Had a question/request around Tender information in Refund Transactions.  \r\n\r\nWhen we were running our files through the Conformance Tool we had to remove the tender tags from the Refund Transactions in the NAXML POS Journal files.  The sample use case provided to us for a Refund Transaction also did not contain any Tender tags.\r\n\r\nIs it possible to allow Tender information about the Refund Transaction in the Refund Event tag.  The Tender tags would be written within the <TransactionLine> tag.','',''),(174,'The question of whether a given maintenance document should have relational integrity has been raised.  Need to address the issue in version 4.0 in some manner.','','Should a given NAXML document include all data required to guarantee the relational integrity of the document as a whole?  In other words, given an ItemMaintenance document, should the parent document also contain MerchandiseCodeMaintenance defining the set of merchandise codes referenced by the items in the ItemMaintenance document, and likewise for any other references, such as TaxStrategyID, etc.?'),(175,'Currently the conformance tool is not set up to test 3.4 documents.  It is still using the 3.3.4 schemas.','','3.4 is latest released version, and there needs to be a way to test conformance.'),(176,'Changes were made to 3.4.0 that required creation of 3.4.1  The release attribute on the documents does not have an enumerated value for this.  ','','Need to be able to show latest release.'),(177,'We need a way to designate that an item is a controlled substance. Retailers who wish to sell such items (e.g. over the counter drugs with ephedrine) are sending transaction data to central sites that maintain consumer purchases of such substances and approval their sell. The POS must determine if a transaction has any of these types of substances included and if so communicate with the central approval agency. This helps law enforcement be proactive with respect to possible leads on illegal drug labs. ','',''),(178,'The nax:Authorization element contains numerous other elements.  Some of these elements appear to duplicate one-another and others appear to be irrelevant, even though there is only a single optional element.\r\n\r\nFor example, in the snippet listed below:\r\n\r\n\r\n	1. The <nax:PreAuthorizationFlag/> field doesn\'t really apply to our POS since we do not log preauth transactions to our TLOG. However, this could be interpreted to mean that the sale was pre-authed prior to completion.\r\n\r\n	2. The <nax:AuthorizationResponseCode/> field is probably used to indicate APPROVED, DECLINED, HOSTDOWN, etc. Since the TLOG only includes APPROVED transactions, this was not deemed to be relevant.\r\n\r\n	3. The <nax:AuthorizationResponseDescription/> field - ditto the above\r\n\r\n	4. The <nax:ApprovalReferenceCode> field is what we ended up deciding to use for the important approval number coming from the Host. The fact that it uses \'Code\' in the name originally led us to use ReferenceNumber instead.\r\n\r\n	5. The <nax:ReferenceNumber/> field - see above comment\r\n\r\n	6. The <nax:ProviderID/>,  <nax:HostAuthorizedFlag/>, <nax:AuthorizationApprovalDescription/>, <nax:AuthorizingTerminalID/>, <nax:ForceOnLineFlag/>, <nax:ElectronicSignature/> fields didn\'t have any obvious meaning to us at this time. Perhaps we could use the Network Terminal ID for the <nax:AuthorizingTerminalID/>,.\r\n\r\n	7. Observation - the Account Number (Encrypted and/or Masked) and Merchant ID are not included.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n				<nax:TransactionLine status=\"normal\">\r\n					<nax:TenderInfo>\r\n						<nax:Tender>\r\n							<nax:TenderCode>creditCards</nax:TenderCode>\r\n							<nax:TenderSubCode>master</nax:TenderSubCode>\r\n						</nax:Tender>\r\n						<nax:TenderAmount currency=\"UNKNOWN\">19.45</nax:TenderAmount>\r\n						<nax:ChangeFlag value=\"no\"/>\r\n						<nax:Authorization>\r\n							<nax:PreAuthorizationFlag/>\r\n							<nax:RequestedAmount currency=\"UNKNOWN\">0</nax:RequestedAmount>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizationResponseCode/>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizationResponseDescription/>\r\n							<nax:ApprovalReferenceCode>123456</nax:ApprovalReferenceCode>\r\n							<nax:ReferenceNumber/>\r\n							<nax:ProviderID/>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizationDate>2007-01-03</nax:AuthorizationDate>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizationTime>14:52:27</nax:AuthorizationTime>\r\n							<nax:HostAuthorizedFlag/>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizationApprovalDescription/>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizingTerminalID/>\r\n							<nax:ForceOnLineFlag/>\r\n							<nax:ElectronicSignature/>\r\n							<nax:AuthorizedChargeAmount currency=\"UNKNOWN\">19.45</nax:AuthorizedChargeAmount>\r\n						</nax:Authorization>\r\n					</nax:TenderInfo>\r\n				</nax:TransactionLine>\r\n\r\n','','A business case needs to be determined.  It is not completely clear as to why this information needs to be in the POS Journal.'),(179,'Right now it appears that only volume or depth is available in a TPM file and we\'d like to be able to allow the POS to report both.  Example','','Some companies want to track both volume and depth for reporting UST reconciliation to other agencies such as the state or oil company.  The example we suggest is:\r\n\r\n<xsd:element name=\"TPMDetail\">\r\n            <xsd:complexType>\r\n                  <xsd:sequence>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"TankID\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"FuelProductID\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"FuelProductDepth\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"FuelProductVolume\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"FuelProductTemperature\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"Ullage\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"WaterDepth\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"WaterVolume\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:element ref=\"ClosingTemperatureCorrectedVolume\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n                        <xsd:group ref=\"extension\"/>\r\n                  </xsd:sequence>\r\n            </xsd:complexType>\r\n      </xsd:element>'),(180,'For the element MarketId, the identRole enumerated value is listed as \"Manufaxturer\" and if spelled \"Manufacturer\" will cause the conformance testing tool to show the file does not comply.','',''),(181,'Expand TaxStrategyID from nax:ID4N to nax:ID16N','','Current format restricts valid values to the range 0 - 9999.  Need to go beyond that value.'),(187,'Need to add the ability to define tenders and connect tender codes.  Specifically need to assign circuit codes to tender codes.\r\n\r\nVaugh Hunt of Chevron has provided a presentation with a suggested set of tender properties.','','This subject has proven too complex to be accomodated with a simple set of standard codes.\r\n\r\nHowever, the committee has assumed that the key field will be either the existing 4.0 tender code or a derivative (i.e. extension) of one of its members.'),(188,'Need to configure tender information in addition to the 4.0 tender codes.','','Group decided to consider the Chevron submission (attached), and potentially make the key field one of the 4.0 tender codes or a derivation of one of them.'),(189,'EthryMethod is currently defined as:\r\n<xs:element name=\"EntryMethod\">\r\n <xs:annotation>\r\n   <xs:documentation>Delineates the method by which an item was identified for the purposes of the transaction, I.e., scanned, PLU, manual entry, etc.</xs:documentation>\r\n </xs:annotation>\r\n   <xs:complexType>\r\n   <xs:attribute name=\"method\" default=\"scan\">\r\n    <xs:simpleType>\r\n     <xs:restriction base=\"nax:id8\">\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"scan\"/>\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"manual\"/>\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"PLU\"/>\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"other\"/>\r\n     </xs:restriction>\r\n    </xs:simpleType>\r\n   </xs:attribute>\r\n  </xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\nWe sould like to add the following values to the Enumeration:\r\n<xs:enumeration value=\"rfid\"/> // smart card like viopay\r\n<xs:enumeration value=\"chip\"/> // smart card where all the info is on the card (used in Asia)\r\n<xs:enumeration value=\"button\"/> (used for item entry like PLU)','','Radiant currently uses other for the value and then adds an extension for the additional values, since these are good for industry, we feel it is a simple schema change to add them.'),(190,'The committee agreed at a face to face meeting May2007 that adding support for carwash is desirable.\r\n\r\nItem Maintenance already supports an item of type “CARW”\r\nAll other carwash sales functionality can already be passed from POS to the BOS using the existing itemLine.  This includes:\r\n•	Pricing\r\n•	Discounts\r\n•	Promotions\r\n•	Wash types (using individual items fro each wash type)\r\n•	Sales location (indoor or outdoor) via the POSID in the journal document\r\nThe committee has decided that reporting carwash codes in the PJR is undesirable.\r\nThe requirement to have a carwash that can only be sold at a specific POS (e.g. cannot be sold outdoors), is not a requirement specific to carwashes and will be discussed separately from carwash specific functionality.\r\n','',''),(191,'Add a maintenance function for fees and review their treatment in the journal.','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDan Rickel \r\nPeter Steele\r\nJeff Shein'),(192,'Add maintenance functions for Merchandise Levels','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDan Rickel \r\nPeter Steele\r\nJeff Shein'),(193,'Add maintenance function for Carwash setup.\r\nRelated to issue #190.','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDan Rickel \r\nPeter Steele\r\nJeff Shein'),(194,'Add maintenance functions for Employee Positions','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDave Egan\r\nGregg Peele\r\nLisa Hester'),(195,'Add maintenance functions for Coupons and review their treatment in the Journal.  ','','Essentially the committee recognizes that there are two types of coupons -- those that can be used as tenders and those that act as discounts.  We\'ll have to disentangle those issues.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nThis feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nDave Egan\r\nGregg Peele\r\nLisa Hester'),(196,'Add maintenance functions for Profit Centers','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nTom Neumayer\r\nRaymond Lugo\r\nPaul Kern'),(197,'Add functions for POS Configuration maintenance.','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nTom Neumayer\r\nRaymond Lugo\r\nPaul Kern'),(198,'Add maintenance functions for Loyalty information, and review the journal support for the feature.','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nTom DiBello\r\nHeather Kinney\r\nCheri Byerley'),(199,'Rework the TaxLevel, TaxIncludes, and TaxStrategy files.  Review journal support.\r\nRelated to issues #0000212, #0000213, #0000214, #0000215, and  #0000217','','This feature is owned by the following TF:\r\nTom DiBello\r\nHeather Kinney\r\nCheri Byerley'),(200,'Rework the MerchandiseCode Maintenance Feature and review support in the journal.','','The first cut at this schema is in SVN.'),(201,'Rework the Item maintenance function and review journal support.','',''),(202,'Rework Maintenance for:\r\nCombo -- related items #170 #169 #162\r\nItemList -- related item #132\r\nMixMatch\r\nand review support in the journal.','',''),(203,'Rework Fuel Grade Maintenance and review support in the journal.','',''),(204,'Rework maintenance functions for Schedule, and review applicable reporting mechanisms (journal?).','',''),(205,'Rework maintenance functions for TankProduct, review reporting (journal?) and make sure integration is smooth with Fuel Rework','','Related to Fuel issue #203'),(206,'Rework maintenance functions for Task, and review reporting (journal?).','',''),(207,'There are two major components, a change to the way the ITT file is used (not the schema) and the Items sales / merchandise code movement files.  I believe this code is currently in the field working with PDI.\r\n\r\nIn the ITT file, we used the linkcode tag to specify the linked item or items.  If the attribute is 1, we link a specific item, 2 we link an item list.  The value is the id of the item or list being linked.  Today we\'ve only implemented the list but we did define the link to a specific item.  \r\n\r\nOne the movement side, here is an example of the ISM file:\r\n·	5 sales of deposit item 12345678 (category 99)\r\n·	6 sales of deposit item 87654321 (category 99)\r\n·	2 redemptions of deposit item 12345678 (category 99)\r\n·	4 redemptions of deposit item 87654321 (category 99)\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<!DOCTYPE NAXML-MovementReport SYSTEM \"NAXML-PBIMovement33.dtd\"> \r\n<NAXML-MovementReport version=\"3.3\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>c03988</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>Radiant Systems</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>RPOS 6.3C6</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<ItemSalesMovement>\r\n		<MovementHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod>2</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod/>\r\n			<BusinessDate>2005-8-12</BusinessDate>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-8-11</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>18:02:56</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-8-12</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>15:23:32</EndTime>\r\n		</MovementHeader>\r\n		<SalesMovementHeader>\r\n			<RegisterID/>\r\n			<CashierID/>\r\n			<TillID/>\r\n			<EmployeeNumber/>\r\n		</SalesMovementHeader>\r\n		<ISMDetail>\r\n			<ItemCode>\r\n				<POSCodeFormat format=\"0\"/>\r\n				<POSCode>40000000235</POSCode>\r\n				<POSCodeModifier>0</POSCodeModifier>\r\n			</ItemCode>\r\n			<ItemID>1234567890</ItemID>\r\n			<Description>Container Deposit - $0.10</Description>\r\n			<MerchandiseCode>12345678</MerchandiseCode>\r\n			<SellingUnits>1</SellingUnits>\r\n			<ISMSellPriceSummary>\r\n				<ActualSalesPrice>0.10</ActualSalesPrice>\r\n				<ISMSalesTotals>\r\n					<DiscountAmount>0</DiscountAmount>\r\n					<DiscountCount/>\r\n					<PromotionAmount/>\r\n					<PromotionCount/>\r\n					<RefundAmount>0.20</RefundAmount>\r\n					<RefundCount>2</RefundCount>\r\n					<SalesQuantity>5</SalesQuantity>\r\n					<SalesAmount>0.50</SalesAmount>\r\n					<TransactionCount>4</TransactionCount>\r\n				</ISMSalesTotals>\r\n			</ISMSellPriceSummary>\r\n		</ISMDetail>\r\n		<ISMDetail>\r\n			<ItemCode>\r\n				<POSCodeFormat format=\"0\"/>\r\n				<POSCode>40000000235</POSCode>\r\n				<POSCodeModifier>0</POSCodeModifier>\r\n			</ItemCode>\r\n			<ItemID>9876543210</ItemID>\r\n			<Description>Container Deposit - $0.15</Description>\r\n			<MerchandiseCode>87654321</MerchandiseCode>\r\n			<SellingUnits>1</SellingUnits>\r\n			<ISMSellPriceSummary>\r\n				<ActualSalesPrice>0.15</ActualSalesPrice>\r\n				<ISMSalesTotals>\r\n					<DiscountAmount>0</DiscountAmount>\r\n					<DiscountCount/>\r\n					<PromotionAmount/>\r\n					<PromotionCount/>\r\n					<RefundAmount>0.60</RefundAmount>\r\n					<RefundCount>4</RefundCount>\r\n					<SalesQuantity>6</SalesQuantity>\r\n					<SalesAmount>0.90</SalesAmount>\r\n					<TransactionCount>5</TransactionCount>\r\n				</ISMSalesTotals>\r\n			</ISMSellPriceSummary>\r\n		</ISMDetail>\r\n	</ItemSalesMovement>\r\n</NAXML-MovementReport>\r\n\r\nAnd one of the MSM\r\n·	5 sales of deposit item 12345678 (category 99)\r\n·	6 sales of deposit item 87654321 (category 99)\r\n·	2 redemptions of deposit item 12345678 (category 99)\r\n·	4 redemptions of deposit item 87654321 (category 99)\r\n  <?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?> \r\n	<NAXML-MovementReport version=\"3.3\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n  		<StoreLocationID>03988</StoreLocationID> \r\n  			<VendorName>Radiant Systems</VendorName> \r\n  			<VendorModelVersion>RPOS 6.3C6</VendorModelVersion> \r\n  	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<MerchandiseCodeMovement>\r\n		<MovementHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod>2</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod/>\r\n			<BusinessDate>2005-8-12</BusinessDate>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-8-11</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>18:02:56</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-8-12</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>15:23:32</EndTime>\r\n  		</MovementHeader>\r\n		<SalesMovementHeader>\r\n  			<RegisterID /> \r\n  			<CashierID /> \r\n  			<TillID /> \r\n  			<EmployeeNumber /> \r\n  		</SalesMovementHeader>\r\n		<MCMDetail>\r\n  			<MerchandiseCode>98</MerchandiseCode> \r\n 			 <MerchandiseCodeDescription>Container Deposits</MerchandiseCodeDescription> \r\n			<MCMSalesTotals>\r\n  				<DiscountAmount>0</DiscountAmount> \r\n  				<DiscountCount /> \r\n  				<PromotionAmount /> \r\n  				<PromotionCount /> \r\n  				<RefundAmount>0.80</RefundAmount> \r\n  				<RefundCount>6</RefundCount> \r\n  				<SalesQuantity>9</SalesQuantity> \r\n  				<SalesAmount>1.20</SalesAmount> \r\n  				<TransactionCount>7</TransactionCount> \r\n  				<VoidAmount /> \r\n  				<VoidCount /> \r\n  				<OpenDepartmentSalesAmount /> \r\n 				 <OpenDepartmentSalesCount /> \r\n 			 </MCMSalesTotals>\r\n  		</MCMDetail>\r\n  </MerchandiseCodeMovement>\r\n  </NAXML-MovementReport>\r\n\r\n\r\nAccording to everything I found, this all fits within the existing 3.4 schema','',''),(208,'in the case where a stored value card authorization or recharge is part of a transaction, the credit network authorization information needs to be attached to the item line, not the tender.  Depending on the methond of payment, the tender may have it\'s own authorization information.\r\n\r\nThe existion authorization information block may be sufficient as an option element under itemline:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"ItemLine\">\r\n <xs:complexType>\r\n  <xs:sequence>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ItemCode\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:SubItemLine\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:Description\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:SerialNumber\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:EntryMethod\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ActualSalesPrice\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:UnitCostPrice\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:MerchandiseCode\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:SellingUnits\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:Discount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:InventoryValuePrice\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:Promotion\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:RegularSellPrice\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:PriceOverride\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:SalesQuantity\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:SalesAmount\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ItemTax\" minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ItemTypeCode\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ItemTypeSubCode\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:TentID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:SalesRestrictCode\" minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:Part\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:PreparationMod\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:Condiment\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:OpenPriceFlag\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:LinkCode\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:Authorization\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n  </xs:sequence>\r\n </xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"Authorization\">\r\n <xs:complexType>\r\n  <xs:sequence>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:PreAuthorizationFlag\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:RequestedAmount\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizationResponseCode\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizationResponseDescription\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ApprovalReferenceCode\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ReferenceNumber\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ProviderID\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizationDate\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizationTime\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:HostAuthorizedFlag\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizationApprovalDescription\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizingTerminalID\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ForceOnLineFlag\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:ElectronicSignature\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizedChargeAmount\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizationVoid\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n  </xs:sequence>\r\n </xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n<xs:element name=\"AuthorizationVoid\">\r\n <xs:complexType>\r\n  <xs:sequence>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:OriginalAmount\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:OriginalApprovalCode\"/>\r\n   <xs:element ref=\"nax:OriginalReferenceNumber\"/>\r\n  </xs:sequence>\r\n </xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n','','For SVC and potentially other store value sales, a host (not the credit host) will confirm the sale with an \"authorization\".'),(209,'Consider that promotions should have a unique ID that is passed in the POS journal on any transaction line to which a given promotion applies.\r\n[Paul Kern, Bill Wade.]','','This could eliminate the need for reason codes. This issue needs to be discussed during the development of the POS journal specification.\r\n'),(210,'Consider adding sales restriction attribute related to the eligibility of an item for a loyalty discount.\r\n[Peter Steele, Bill Wade] ','','This issue needs to be discussed during the development of the discount maintenance specification.\r\n'),(211,'Rework Employee Maintenance','',''),(212,'How are tax exemptions setup on the POS and is there a requirement for the BO to configure those exemptions. ','',''),(213,'Determine how to handle taxes that apply to items that have already been taxed in circumstances such as the Canadian tax system.','','Canadian tax situation.  Related issue 0000199.'),(214,'Describe how we would represent a tax which is not based on a single rate but on a set of rates based on a criteria such as number purchased or amount purchased etc.','','Tax rules can change based on quantity purchased (ref. Canadian Tax (doughnut rule)).'),(215,'Is it necessary for the BO to configure how the POS would handle Tax Forgiveness scenarios.  Or is this something that would only be reported.','','If foodstamps are used to purchase an item, tax is forgiven rather than exempted.\r\nRelated to issue 0000199.'),(216,'From the f2f 2007-05-16:\r\n\r\nThe committee agreed to define a maintenance file which contains a list of item exceptions for specific PLUS to restrict their sale at specific POSs. This may be considered as the structure for other sales restrictions in future discussions. This is analogous to the item list used in mix-match combos.\r\n\r\n\r\n','','Exceptions where a PLU may have a different price, discount, promotion or taxes outside than inside is proposed to be achieved by having separate items. \r\n'),(217,'The 3.4 version of NAXML supports percentage tax levels, but doesn\'t define a format for breakpoint tax tables. ','','This format is still a popular legislatively dictated way to define required sales taxes.'),(218,'This item is related to #174 (closed) but acknowledges the need for documentation explaining how systems should handle issues reported when data is transmitted and then fails to be accepted for various reasons.','',''),(219,'A better definition of end of day -- data included, algorithms involved, and timing requirements -- needs to be produced.','',''),(220,'We need to recommend an approach for mapping information to a business day, with recommended practices for vendors.  Network issues have an unfortunate impact here, as do installation issues.','',''),(221,'Proposed\r\nlocalacct\r\nrent\r\nvendorpmt-beer\r\nvendorpmt-coke\r\nlotterywinner\r\nbillpmt\r\nbillpmt-phone\r\ngeneric','',''),(222,'1) Improve commonality\r\n2) use \"venitian blind\" construction\r\n3) shorten identifiers\r\n4) reduce depth','',''),(223,'This issue is related to #188 which will be considered separately.','',''),(224,'This issue is entered in response to issue #123, in order to add adequate information to identify meter readings and tank levels associated with price changes and product deliveries respectively.','','Support Fuel Price Change and Fuel Delivery scenarios.'),(225,'for the telcon','','			<xs:enumeration value=\"document\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"document-wellFormed\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"document-schemaValid\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"document-version\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"processing\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"processing-date\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"processing-action\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"processing-datasetSize\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"processing-partialCommitProhibited\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data-linkCheck\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data-valueRange\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data-length\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data-enumeration\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data-requiredField\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"data-notAllowed\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"system\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"system-access\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"system-write\"/>\r\n			<xs:enumeration value=\"system-fault\"/>'),(226,'3.4 has discounts modified by a reason code.  4.0 may need discounts for a) line items and b) transactions, with various categories of each.','','The 3.4 mechanism is not adequate for reporting.'),(227,'I would like to be able to centrally manage the POS receipt layout.','',''),(228,'Refactor movement reports to create a DayPeriod movement report structure.','','See CR220'),(229,'Refactor movement reports to create a ShiftPeriod movement report structure','','See CR220'),(230,'Refactor movement reports to create a CashierPeriod movement report.','','See CR220'),(231,'Refactor movement reports to create a DayPart movement report structure.','','See CR220'),(232,'Create an acknowledgement document structure by which a receiving system can inform the sending system that it has received and processed a set of movement reports or POS journal','','Will provide a positive response to the POS that it can mark the reports as completed.'),(233,'EITDetail record currently contains an optional SalesCommissionData structure.  The comittee feels that this is a function of the back office to be calculated as a result of transaction data and does not need to be pushed to the POS.','',''),(234,'Need to refine UOM designations so that UOM uses are separate from \"each\" or pack designations, and so that they are limited to measure germane to the cstore environment. ','','From the f2f 2008-03-26:\r\n\r\nGeneral definition; an identifier added to a number which gives it meaning. \r\n\r\nThe current schema assumes a US centric schema and does not allow a default UOM to be specified.  Consider currency as a UOM. \r\n\r\nLocale dependencies are currency & volume.  Length & weight are selling package specific.  Any of these UOMs can be specified as UOM / time.\r\n\r\nThe group thinks that several of the UOM enumerations may not be used and can be removed from the schema.\r\n\r\nTime \r\nSpeed \r\nSales \r\n\r\nSales quantity should be expressed in terms of a choice of an integer value ( 1 - ea)  OR a dimensional quantity (decimal value) combined with a UOM attribute (1.2 oz).\r\n\r\nDocuments should include default currency code and default fuel (wet stock) volume UOM in the document header.  Wet stock should have an attribute to allow the UOM to be specified, if it is not specified, the default in the header is assumed.  The outer most element will contain these as attributes.\r\n\r\nMr. Wade would like to see currency and weight UOM modified to use the ISO accepted terms.  There is an open question that if we use ISO terms, do we need to recommend people supporting the standard purchase the ISO standards documents.\r\n\r\nKWH needs to be maintained for battery charges.\r\n\r\nThe goal is to simplify the schema to remove UOMs not used.\r\n\r\n'),(235,'Add fields and methods to allow BackOffice Systems to support Food Service functions through POS Terminals, and for POS Terminals to report on Food Service related data.','','C-Store POS systems have to support food service through Kiosk and through conventional means.  Supporting these activities requires introducing some new terminology and data fields.'),(236,'LineItem/PurchaseOrderInfo/PurchaseOrderNumber is defined as an integer.  It needs to be alphanumeric, as permitted in X12','','Suppliers that accept alphanumeric PO numbers and are obligated to provide PO information back to the retailer on invoices are unable to build a schema-valid invoice file.'),(237,'Modify the schema extension mechanism to utilize a unique extension element name at each extension point, referencing an element definition in a separate user-modifiable schema document.','','Provides a straight-forward uniform mechanism for the introduction of proprietary extensions that facilitates code generation from the resulting schema.  See the attached example, containing a new NAXML-ExtensionGroups34.xsd.'),(238,'Change NAXML-BusDoc/Invoice/Invoice/LineItem from minOccurs=\"1\" to minOccurs=\"0\".','','This will permit the transmission of invoices for which the invoiced amount consists only of allowances and charges provided in the InvoiceSummary/InvoiceTotals.  At least one wholesaler is using this to transmit charges and credits for totes.'),(239,'Determine business requirements related to item tax overrides at the POS.','',''),(240,'TaxLevelMovement needs to include support for reporting other taxes included in the base for the calculation of tax collected.  Other tax amounts included should be reported by tax level ID.','',''),(241,'Tax holidays are implemented by temporarily altering the tax strategy ID for the affected items.','',''),(242,'Modify the RetailPrice element used in RetailUnitPricing to permit an optional multiplier attribute as illustrated.\r\n    <xs:element name=\"RetailPrice\">\r\n        <xs:annotation>\r\n            <xs:appinfo>\r\n                <psd:classification>Elements</psd:classification>\r\n            </xs:appinfo>\r\n            <xs:documentation>The retail price of the item.</xs:documentation>\r\n            <xs:documentation source=\"docs/Dict-RetailPrice.png\"/>\r\n        </xs:annotation>\r\n        <xs:complexType>\r\n            <xs:simpleContent>\r\n                <xs:extension base=\"xs:string\">\r\n                    <xs:attribute name=\"currency\" type=\"pcats:iso4217_Currency\"/>\r\n                    <xs:attribute name=\"UOMBasis\"/>\r\n                    <xs:attribute name=\"multiplier\" type=\"xs:nonNegativeInteger\" use=\"optional\"/>\r\n                </xs:extension>\r\n            </xs:simpleContent>\r\n        </xs:complexType>\r\n    </xs:element>\r\n','','Some vendors provide retailers the ability to specify retail pricing as \"3 for $1.00\".  The attribute will permit them to communicate that pricing multiplier when needed.'),(243,'Tracking of issues on the datamodel','',''),(244,'Final documentation for the Tenders Dataset.','',''),(245,'Final documentation for the Tenders Dataset.','',''),(246,'Final specification for the Taxes Dataset.','','');
