INSERT INTO `mantis_bugnote_text_table` VALUES (1,'Just as a comment to this request...\r\n \r\nI believe it would make the specification easier to implement if the data dictionary specified the contents of the Sales Amount field as gross vs. net rather than making it soft, based on the value of an attribute.  Why make client (receiver) software put in conditional code to handle the various contents instead of one set of code that translates the value to conform to the client software\'s needs?\r\nRegards, \r\nSam W. Davis \r\nV.P. of Development \r\nFactor, a W.R. Hess Company \r\n(405) 224-6062 x201 \r\nsdavis@factor.com'),(3,'That\'s an implementation convention that cannot be enforced by the schema, therefore you are depending on the application producing the instance documents to conform to the convention, without providing any means for the consuming application to verify whether it actually does so or not.  The attribute could easily be defaulted to gross or net, whichever is most prevalent, to allow applications that conform to the convention to produce the document without the additional attribute.\r\n\r\nBill Wade'),(14,'Reviewed by Change Review Committee\r\nAction deferred to full POS/Back Office committee meeting Jun 8 - 10 in Atlanta.\n\nedited on: 05-27-04 15:43'),(15,'Reviewed by Change Request Committee 5/27/2004\r\nBWade recommended allowing a value of zeros.\r\nJohn Pratt commented that values in the ranges 560 to 590 and 800 to 900 are not valid per the schema.  A review of the schema reveals the enumerations are drawn from the NACS Payment Systems Product Codes specification.  The range 560 to 599 are labeled \"Undefined Merchandise\" in that specification.  The range 600 - 799 is labeled \"Reserved for future use\". The range 800 - 899 are labeled \"Reserved - Proprietary Use\".\r\nRecommend adding codes 560- 590 for undefined merchandise and 800 to 899 for proprietary use to the enumerations, as well as code 000 (defined in the NACS specification as \"Not Used\".\n\nedited on: 05-27-04 15:18'),(16,'Reviewed by Change Request Committee 05/27/2004\r\nAll parties present are depending on the presence of this attribute.\r\nRecommend adding in version 3.3.3.'),(17,'Reviewed by Change Request Committee 5/27/2004\r\nThe definition of the SalesAmount element in the schema is ambiguous. Committee recommends altering the structure of MSMSalesTotals to allow a choice of GrossSalesAmount or NetSalesAmount, and likewise a choice of GrossSalesQuantity or NetSalesQuantity, thus making the usage of the elements explicit.'),(18,'Reviewed and approved by change request committee 5/27/2004'),(19,'Reviewed by change request committee and approved for inclusion in version 3.3.3\n\nedited on: 05-27-04 15:43'),(20,'While changing to either NetSalesQuantity/GrossSalesQuantity and NetSalesAmount/GrossSalesAmount may be preferred I don\'t see how this can be done without making this change break version 3.3 and making it necessary to upgrade to version 3.4.  However, adding an attribute to both SalesQuantity and SalesAmount that is #IMPLIED would preserve compatibility with version 3.3.  There is no authority to move from 3.3 to 3.4 at this time.'),(21,'While changing to either NetSalesQuantity/GrossSalesQuantity and NetSalesAmount/GrossSalesAmount may be preferred I don\'t see how this can be done without making this change break version 3.3 and making it necessary to upgrade to version 3.4.  However, adding an attribute to both SalesQuantity and SalesAmount that is #IMPLIED would preserve compatibility with version 3.3.  There is no authority to move from 3.3 to 3.4 at this time.'),(22,'This has been resolve in version 3.3.3 with the addition of an attribute of name on the element POSCodeModifier as optional.'),(23,'This has been resolve in version 3.3.3 with the addition of an attribute of name on the element POSCodeModifier as optional.'),(24,'Added in version 3.3.3'),(25,'Added in version 3.3.3'),(26,'Resolved by adding two elements in version 3.3.3 - SalesAmountGross and SalesAmountNet and making it a choice of (SalesAmount | SalesAmountGross | SalesAmountNet) and by adding comment that SalesAmount is deprecatd and will be removed in the next version.'),(27,'Resolved by adding to the enumerations in version 3.3.3'),(28,'Resolved by adding to the Payment Systems Product Codes enumeration list all blank or reserved codes.'),(29,'The spelling error was corrected in the dtd and the element now reads \"AuthorizedChargeAmount\" - this matches the xsd.'),(30,'The element \"F\" was removed from the dtd. The xsd and dtd should match.'),(31,'Changed sequence of elements in the content model to match the xsd.'),(32,'The element State in the dtd has been changed to StateOrProvince to match the xsd.'),(33,'The element State in the dtd has been changed to StateOrProvince to match the xsd.'),(34,'change made to dtd to make UOMBasis uom as per the xsd.'),(35,'all attributes in dtd changed to lower case for first letter of the first word.'),(36,'closed'),(37,'See problem with adding these enumerations with the addition of other to not preclude any existing implementation.'),(38,'Should be \"no\" problem adding with the addition of \"other\"'),(39,'There are other possible values and at least one other is being used - \"Dealer\".  It is possible to add enumerations of \"location, dealer, other\" but there would still need to be agreement among trading partners as to which value will be used.'),(40,'This change will be made in version 1.5.1 and Credit and Debit will be added as enumeration values.  Sign should not be used - credit/debit should indicate the value.'),(41,'This change will be made in version 1.5.1 to add enumerated values of \"Automated, Manual and Other\"'),(42,'This change will be made in version 1.5.1 to add enumerated values of \"Credit and Debit\".'),(43,'In actual usage there are many different values being used for \"CardType\" including specific card company names as well as generic names such as \"proprietary\", \"debitcard\" etc. A list of enumerated values would be quite extensive and would not serve the purpose desired of avoiding trading partner differences.\r\nCardType is meant to be a summary of all of the cards within that type. Here is an actual snippet:\r\n<CardType identType=\"WEX\" quantity=\"3\" grossAmount=\"89.18\" netAmount=\"86.73\">\r\n<AllowanceOrCharge>\r\n<AllowanceOrChargeReason>Card Processing Fee</AllowanceOrChargeReason>\r\n<ChargeAmt UOMBasis=\"PerCard\">2.45</ChargeAmt>\r\n</AllowanceOrCharge>\r\n</CardType>\r\nThe grossAmount of 89.18 minus the ChargeAmt (charge indicating minus) of 2.45 equals the netAmount of 86.73.  There shouldn\'t be a difference between grossAmount and netAmount unless there is an Allowance or Charge Amount shown.  It was for this reason that the consturct was as it is, that is, without a \"Credit\" or \"Debit\" enumeration.  However, it is clear that this could be made clearer and will be referred to the committee for resolution.'),(44,'Possible change for 2.0 - will be referred to the committee for resolution.'),(45,'Enumeration values of \"Credit\" and \"Debit\" will be added in version 1.5.1'),(46,'Refer to committee for resolution.'),(47,'Made a mistake.  Not in Movement, in POSJournal'),(48,'ChevronTexaco WILL require Namespace declarations for all instance documents. If we take Namespace requirements out then the standard is very weak and of lesser value to retailers.   \r\n\r\nGeneral comment is that the standards are too weak already.  By this I mean that there are multiple ways to implement some functionality.  For example fuels can be treated as a dry stock item or more appropiately as a fuel item.'),(49,'The question is how in a Cstore will the Name space be resolved to the URL?  So if I have this as the namespace, as it needs to be in the conformance tool:\r\nxmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\r\nNAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\r\n\r\nHow would a cstore validate against this, unless they have an internet connection? My thought is that the consuming application would do a validation against a local copy of the schema.'),(50,'Made content of SalesRestrictionGroup a choice of either (one only) SalesRestrictCode or SalesRestriction.'),(51,'Added EmployeeInformationMaintenance to the end of the sequence for NAXML-MaintenanceRequest, min occurs 0, max occurs unbounded.'),(52,'Made TillID optional (min occurs 0) as suggested.'),(53,'Made PumpTestReason and PumpTesterID optional in PumpTestDetail'),(54,'Made Tender/TenderSubCode minOccurs=\"0\" in PBIDictionary'),(55,'Made SafeDropDetail/EnvelopeID and SafeDropDetail/DropNumber minOccurs=\"0\" in POSJournal'),(56,'Added clockIn and clockOut as enumerations for punchReasonBase in PBIBaseTypes'),(57,'Made DeviceID, TaskID, EntryMethod minOccurs=\"0\" in TimeClockDetail in POSJournal'),(58,'<!--TenderSummaryMovement structures-->\r\n	<xs:element name=\"TenderSummaryMovement\">\r\n		<xs:annotation>\r\n			<xs:documentation>Tender Summary Movement (TSM) - Contains those data elements the POS system needs to send to the BO system to report “Tender” summary level detail for all financial transactions.</xs:documentation>\r\n		</xs:annotation>\r\n		<xs:complexType>\r\n			<xs:sequence>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:MovementHeader\"/>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:SalesMovementHeader\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TSMDetail\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n			</xs:sequence>\r\n		</xs:complexType>\r\n	</xs:element>\r\n	<xs:element name=\"TSMDetail\">\r\n		<xs:complexType>\r\n			<xs:sequence>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:Tender\"/>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TSMSalesTotals\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n				<xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n			</xs:sequence>\r\n		</xs:complexType>\r\n	</xs:element>\r\n	<xs:element name=\"TSMSalesTotals\">\r\n		<xs:complexType>\r\n			<xs:sequence>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:Currency\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderOpenBalance\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>     <!--   Open Balance          -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderNetAmount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>       <!-- + TenderNetAmount       -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderCloseBalance\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>    <!-- = TenderCloseBalance    -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderCountedBalance\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>  <!-- - TenderCountedBalance  -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderOverShortAmount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/> <!-- = TenderOverShortAmount -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>        \r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:LoanAmount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>            <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:LoanCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>             <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:RefundAmount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>          <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:RefundCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>           <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:VoidAmount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>            <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:VoidCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>             <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:DropAmount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>            <!-- Statistical -->\r\n				<xs:element ref=\"nax:DropCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>             <!-- Statistical -->\r\n			</xs:sequence>\r\n		</xs:complexType>\r\n	</xs:element>'),(59,'Add ProhibitTender to SalesRestriction, minOccurs=\"0\", maxOccurs=\"unbounded\", defined as follows:\r\n<ProhibitTender>\r\n  <Tender>\r\n    <TenderCode/>\r\n    <TenderSubCode/> (optional)\r\n  </Tender>\r\n</ProhibitTender>'),(60,'Added as detailed in Bill Wade\'s note.'),(61,'Added TenderMovementSummary'),(62,'Submitted on behalf of Bhanu @ VeriFone.'),(63,'Added BatchSummaryMovement to NAXML-MovementReport'),(64,'The following declaration is required to form a valid XML instance document (using a NAXML-MaintenanceRequest as an example):\r\n<NAXML-MaintenanceRequest \r\nxmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\" \r\nxmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" \r\nxsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\r\nNAXML-PBIMaintenance33.xsd\">\r\n\r\nThis sets nax as the default namespace, eliminating the need for the nax: qualifier on the element tagnames.  The instance document is validated against the schema document at the pathname specified in xsi:schemaLocation.'),(65,'Set ItemLine/Discount, FuelLine/Discount, and MerchandiseCodeLine to maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" in POSJournal.  Per Lisa Hester\'s request, did the same for Promotion'),(66,'Added PaymentSystemsProductCode as an optional child of FGTData to allow specification of network product code in conjunction with a ServiceLevelCode.'),(67,'Made Discount unbounded under FuelLine'),(68,'Added pointRelease base type with enumerations 3.3.0, 3.3.1, 3.3.2, 3.3.3, and 3.3.4 to PBIBaseTypes.  Added release as an optional attribute on NAXML-MovementReport, NAXML-MaintenanceRequest, and NAXML-POSJournal'),(69,'To correct the Release field.'),(70,'Corrected the Release field in the CR from \"unassigned\" to \"current\"'),(74,'Completed in version 1.5.1'),(75,'There are approximately 1400 TCN\'s and the list is updated monthly by the IRS.  It would be hard to maintain an xsd unless published by the IRS and referred to by NAXML-FuelBillOfLading.xsd.'),(76,'Resolved in version 1.5.1.'),(77,'Resolved in Version 1.5.1'),(78,'Resolved in version 1.5.1'),(79,'Resolved in version 1.5.1'),(80,'Resolved in version 1.5.1'),(81,'Resolved in version 1.5.1'),(82,'resolved in version 1.5.1.'),(83,'resolved in version 1.5.1'),(84,'Need resolution.'),(85,'Need to resolve.'),(86,'I concur with Chip.  In some cases, a combo is priced by means of the application of discounts or price overrides at the component level.\r\n\r\nSuppose, for example, that I want to promote a line of fresh sandwiches.  The sandwiches vary in price from $1.99 (a hot dog) to $2.29 (a meatball sub).  I want to offer a free 12oz canned soda to anyone who buys a sandwich.  But I don\'t want to sell all the sandwiches at the same price.  So I set up the promo as shown below:\r\n\r\nCombo 1 - Fresh Sandwich Promo\r\nItem List 1: Sandwiches\r\nItem List 1 Discount Type: None\r\n\r\nItem List 2: 12oz Beverage\r\nItem List 2 Discount Type: Percent\r\nItem List 2 Discount Percent: 100\r\n\r\nIn NAXML, this would look like the following (with ComboPrice included)\r\n    <CBTDetail>\r\n      <Promotion>\r\n        <PromotionID>1</PromotionID>\r\n      </Promotion>\r\n      <ComboDescription>Fresh Sandwich Promo</ComboDescription>\r\n      <ComboPrice/>\r\n      <ComboList>\r\n        <ComboItemList>\r\n          <ItemListID>1</ItemListID>\r\n          <ComboItemQuantity>1</ComboItemQuantity>\r\n          <ComboItemDiscountAllocation type=\"amount\">0</ComboItemDiscountAllocation>\r\n        </ComboItemList>\r\n        <ComboItemList>\r\n          <ItemListID>2</ItemListID>\r\n          <ComboItemQuantity>1</ComboItemQuantity>\r\n          <ComboItemDiscountAllocation type=\"percent\">100</ComboItemDiscountAllocation>\r\n        </ComboItemList>\r\n      </ComboList>\r\n    </CBTDetail>\r\n\r\nAs an alternative for specifying a discount of 100% on item list 2, you could specify a ComboItemUnitPrice of zeros.\r\n\r\nNote that ComboItemDiscountAllocation and ComboItemUnitPrice should be mutually exclusive, as I\'ve used them here.\r\n\r\nThis usage convention does have one drawback, that being the use of ComboItemDiscountAllocation to specify a component level discount in the absence of ComboPrice.  When ComboPrice is present, ComboItemDiscountAllocation is assumed to represent how much of the overall combo discount should be applied to the items from the indicated component list.  When ComboPrice is absent, ComboItemDiscountAllocation is assumed to specify a discount amount or percent to be applied to the regular price of the component.  A subtle difference, to be sure, but worth noting.\n\nedited on: 02-16-05 16:21'),(87,'I concur - I just submitted the same request.'),(88,'The enumerations for the type attribute on ComboItemDiscountAllocation are missing.'),(89,'Recommend the following content model for CBTDetail (make ComboPrice minOccurs=\"0\"):\r\n  <xs:element name=\"CBTDetail\">\r\n    <xs:complexType>\r\n      <xs:sequence>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:Promotion\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n        <xs:group ref=\"nax:SalesRestrictionGroup\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:LinkCode\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboDescription\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboPrice\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboList\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:StartDate\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:StartTime\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:StopDate\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:StopTime\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:WeekdayAvailability\" minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:LotLimit\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:TransactionLimit\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboPromotions\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:Priority\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n        <xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n      </xs:sequence>\r\n    </xs:complexType>\r\n  </xs:element>'),(90,'Enumerations are present - user error.'),(91,'Duplicate request.'),(92,'Recommend the following model for ComboItemList(as it was in 3.3.3):\r\n  <xs:element name=\"ComboItemList\">\r\n    <xs:complexType>\r\n      <xs:sequence>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:ItemListID\"/>\r\n	<xs:choice>\r\n          <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboItemQuantity\"/>\r\n          <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboItemUnitPrice\"/>\r\n	</xs:choice>\r\n        <xs:element ref=\"nax:ComboItemDiscountAllocation\"/>\r\n        <xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n      </xs:sequence>\r\n    </xs:complexType>\r\n  </xs:element>'),(93,'Recommend a new child for OtherEvent. Defer to 4.0'),(94,'Need feedback on this request - which document and content model does it need to be added to?'),(95,'mzeise - 2/21:  By \"ComboUnitPrice\" I mean the \"ComboItemUnitPrice\" in the ComboMaintenance node.  Thanks!\r\n\r\nmzeise - 2/25: I realized it says Data Dictionary but should be in the Maintenance schema that I\'m requesting the change.  Thanks.\n\nedited on: 02-25-05 13:52'),(96,'Are you looking at 3.3.3 or 3.3.4?  In 3.3.3 this is a choice, either have ComboItemUnitPrice, or have ComboItemDiscountAllocation.  This is how it is supposed to be in 3.3.4 as well, but was mistkenly set to have both required.  This is addressed in CR 0000074 and was recommended to be changed back to choice by the group that met to discuss it.'),(97,'Duplicate of 0000073'),(98,'Set content model for CBTDetail to make ComboPrice minOccurs=\"0\"'),(99,'Defer to 4.0, with the recommendation for the creation of content models for specific use cases, e.g., ItemAdd, ItemAddChange, ItemPricing, etc.'),(100,'Corrected to max value of 99999999'),(101,'Corrected ComboItemList to require a choice of ComboItemUnitPrice or ComboItemDiscountAllocation'),(102,'Change Review Committee defers this question to the working committee.'),(103,'Added \"preferredTender\" as an enumeration on discountReasonBase in NAXML-PBIBaseTypes33.xsd'),(104,'John Hervey - can you handle this one, or do we need to defer it to a working committee meeting?'),(105,'There were not enough parties on the change review call to constitute a quorum.  Should we defer this issue to a working committee meeting?'),(106,'There is a problem with using \"tenderTypeDiscount\" as an enumeration.  The base for the element is \"nax:16\" - this enumeration has 18 letters.  It has been shortened to \"tenderTypeDiscnt\".'),(107,'Are more specific product codes needed for Ultra Low Sulfer and what about Non-Taxable?  Will B100 ever by sold in the retail environment?\r\n\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel\r\n\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B2\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B5\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B10\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B20\r\n\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B2 Non-Taxable\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B5 Non-Taxable\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B10 Non-Taxable\r\nUltra Low Sulfur Diesel B20 Non-Taxable\r\n\r\nedited on: 03-31-05 08:53\n\nedited on: 03-31-05 08:53'),(108,'ChevronTexaco concurrs with this proposed change.'),(109,'As an accounting standard, the opposite of a paid-out is a paid-in and vice versa.  Therefore in keeping with a standard practice if a cashier makes a mistake by entering the wrong safe drop value then, shouldn’t they be doing a paid-in back into the drawer and not a refund of a safe drop?   A refund of a sale is much different than the reversal of a financial transaction.   Similar refund issues arise with other special transactions such as pump tests.  In each case, a specific transaction should be used to balance the cash (as in refunds of a paid out) or the inventory and sales (as in a pump test)   Opening up refunds of paid outs has a loss prevention implication.   If a POS system does allow a refund of a paid out, this could be translated to a paid in to allow the current POS functionality to remain the same, but the interface can encourage the best practice for vendors.'),(110,'DataMax strongly supports this request. The need for this status is important in some of our markets. This is a simple way of tracking a mistake. Forcing a paid in when no cash was removed seems pointless. We need to track errors in the keying habits of cashiers. Logging a Paid In will generate erroneous tracking data when you are doing a cash reconciliation.'),(111,'The difference here is that paid-ins and paid-outs represent money entering/leaving the store.  Safe drops represent money moving within the store, from a drawer to a safe (or vice versa).\r\n\r\nPaid ins/outs affect a given drawer and overall cash, whereas safe drops do not affect overall cash.\r\n\r\nUsing a paid-in to correct an errant drop would leave the safe balance out of whack, for those who track it.\r\n\r\nI am tempted to concur, but I am not clear on the difference between Cancel, Void and Refund.  In my mind, Refund is mutually exclusive of the others.  If one allows an original transaction to be \"un-done\", its status would be Void or perhaps Cancel, to retain knowledge of its occurance even though it affects nothing.  No need for Refund, the status of the original is simply changed.\r\n\r\nIf instead one always offsets a transaction with a correcting transaction (preferred), then Cancel and Void are not needed.\r\n\r\nAre we including all of these status codes to accommodate both approaches?\n\nedited on: 06-09-05 09:30'),(112,'I think that \"Void\" or \"Cancel\" would be the proper term for the sitation as it is described -- rather than \"return.\" Both Void and Cancel are already supported for financial event.'),(113,'Use of preferredTender as an enumeration was accepted by pmkern'),(114,'It is agreed that this element shall be defined as containing the sum of the line items of a transaction, net of item level discounts, promotions, etc., but before the application of transaction level discounts, promotions, taxes, etc.\r\n\r\nIt is also noted that TransactionTotalGrandAmount and TransactionTotalNetAmount have the same definition in the dictionary.  Resolution of this ambiguity should be addressed in version 4.0'),(115,'The recommendation of the working group in a case where a returned product results in the refund of sales tax to the customer such that the net sales tax amount is due to the customer, the POS system should sign the sales tax amount in the TransactionTax as a negative amount, and the parent TransactionLine element should have a status of \"normal\".'),(116,'Added the extension element (defined in NAXML-PBIDictionary33.xsd) at the end of the content model for NAXML-MaintenanceRequest.'),(117,'Added an extension element (defined in NAXML-PBIDictionary33.xsd) to the end of the content model for NAXML-MovementReport.'),(118,'The working group questions the need for a status of refund on a FinancialEvent.  It seems as though the void status could be used to communicate the reversal of a preceding transaction, and the working group recommends that as a solution with respect to the use of version 3.3.  A new change request has been entered for version 4.0 to add FinancialEventDetail as an optional child of VoidEvent.  This would permit the reversal of the orginal transaction with a link to the original transaction as well.'),(119,'The working group agrees.  CR assigned to John Hervey for resolution.'),(120,'Withdrawn.  Duplicate CR 83 already entered for version 4.0'),(121,'Both TillID and EnvelopeID were removed in 3.3.4 of the use case for the Conformance Testing Tool.'),(122,'Correct fields'),(123,'These elements will be made optional in 4 use cases and testers will be notified when the conformance testing tool has been updated.'),(124,'Will modify schema documents to make the version attribute on NAXML-POSJournal, NAXML-MovementReport, NAXML-MaintenanceRequest to make it required, but not fix that value at \"3.3\".  The implication is that systems will validate that the version attribute contains the value they are expecting, rather than relying on schema validation to invalidate the document.'),(125,'The content model for TransactionLine contains a choice of (ItemLine, MerchandiseCodeLine,FuelPrepayLine,FuelLine,MoneyOrderLine,WashCodeLine,PromotionReward,PromotionTrigger,TransactionTax,TenderInfo,CustomerID,RoundingAmount,DiscountLine).  The choice itself is marked as unbounded, when in fact it should allow one and only one occurrence of any element from that choice.  This is an unintended construct, and a comment will be added to the schema indicating that the TransactionLine element should not contain multiple children from that choice.'),(126,'Assigned to John Hervey, with the instruction to make these two use cases non-Core, but create new use cases for fuel grade price maintenance by grade, rather than by fueling position.'),(127,'Here is an example of what we would like this new CheckCashDetail structure to look like:\r\n\r\n<CheckCashDetail>\r\n	  <CheckNumber/> (required)\r\n	  <CheckCashFeeCollected/> (required)\r\n	  <TenderInfo/> (allow existing TenderInfo element and children to be used by CheckCashDetail)\r\n</CheckCashDetail>\r\n\r\nWithin TenderInfo we could store the check amount, cash amount paid, and all information about the Customer (Name, ID, BirthDate, etc) in CustomerID and AccountInfo. So, the only things we need added are CheckCashDetail with child elements CheckNumber and CheckCashFeeCollected, and the existing TenderInfo as the third child element.\r\n\r\nAll of this could be stored in TenderInfo, except for the check number, but it is not really a Sale, Void, or Refund event. It is a FinancialEvent, which is why we would like this new element added.\r\n\r\nOh, and I don\'t really have a preference if it is \"CheckCashingDetail\" or \"CheckCashDetail\". \r\n\r\nLet me know if you have any questions or concerns.\n\nedited on: 08-11-05 17:16'),(128,'Mr. David Godwin of VeriFone (david_g3@verifone.com) agreed in the 08/18/2005 to provide an example on http://pcats.jot.com via an FAQ document.'),(129,'This issue will be dealt with in version 4.0'),(130,'Discussed in teleconference 08/18/2005.  Ms. Kinney to circulate an XML document fragment detailing the structure she would like to see.'),(131,'Reviewed in 08/18/2005 teleconference. Ms. Kinney to go back to her subject matter expert for clarification of the business requirements.  BatchDetail may not provide adequate support for money order movement summaries.'),(132,'Reviewed in 08/18/2005 teleconference.  Voted to change POSCodeModifier name attribute to type nax:description10'),(133,'Reviewed in 08/18/2005 teleconference.  Mr. Kern to circulate a revised use case document.'),(134,'Reviewed in 08/18/2005 teleconference.  Ms. Kinney to circulate a sample instance document, assembled from existing dictionary elements (FPMDetail?) to the extent possible.  She will also key a request for version 4.0 for the same issue, but in version 4.0 we may use a complex type as a basis for both FPMDetail and the new structure Ms. Kinney needs.\n\nedited on: 08-18-05 14:17'),(135,'Reviewed in 08/18/2005 teleconference.  Change MMTDetail/WeekdayAvailability to maxOccurs=\"unbounded\".'),(136,'Reviewed in 08/18/2005 teleconference.  Ms. Kinney to circulate a sample instance document.'),(137,'My opinion is that the intent was this amount was to be the total price at the given mixmatch quantity. I think the name of it is bad if that\'s the case, but if that\'s not what it means, then the price book will probably have to work backwards to figure out the discount amount, given I would think mix-match prices are usually specified in terms of the quantity and price, such as 3 for a dollar, 2 for $0.99, etc. So $0.99 isn\'t the discount at all, it\'s the _price_. It looks like the node used to be called MixMatchPrice, so I don\'t know why we changed it.'),(138,'Per yesterday\'s conference call, here is my proposal for the new CheckCashDetail element for the POSJournal schema. \r\n\r\nI have it set up so there are two tenders, one for the check amount, with a ChangeFlag of \"no\", and one for the cash dispensed with a ChangeFlag of \"no\".  Is this the correct usage of the ChangeFlag?  Should the ChangeFlag for the cash dispensed be \"yes\"? Perhaps we want the cash dispensed amount to be negative with the TenderSubCode just as cash?\r\n\r\nXML Document Example:\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<FinancialEvent>\r\n			<FinancialEventDetail status=\"normal\">\r\n				<CheckCashDetail>\r\n					<CheckNumber>1234</CheckNumber>\r\n					<CheckCashFeeCollected>2.00</CheckCashFeeCollected>\r\n					<TenderInfo>\r\n						<Tender>\r\n							<TenderCode>check</TenderCode>\r\n							<TenderSubCode>commercialCheck</TenderSubCode>\r\n						</Tender>\r\n						<TenderAmount>20.00</TenderAmount>\r\n						<ChangeFlag value=\"no\"/>\r\n						<AccountInfo>\r\n							<AccountID>1344863</AccountID>\r\n							<AccountName>John A Doe</AccountName>\r\n							<AccountFirstName>John</AccountFirstName>\r\n							<AccountMiddleName>A</AccountMiddleName>\r\n							<AccountLastName>Doe</AccountLastName>\r\n						</AccountInfo>\r\n						<CustomerID>\r\n							<CashierBypassedFlag value=\"no\"/>\r\n							<EntryMethod method=\"manual\"/>\r\n							<PersonalID idType=\"driversLicense\">1234-5678-90</PersonalID>\r\n							<IDExpirationDate>2006-09-01</IDExpirationDate>\r\n							<IDIssuingAuthority>Indiana</IDIssuingAuthority>\r\n							<BirthDate>1960-09-01</BirthDate>\r\n						</CustomerID>\r\n					</TenderInfo>\r\n					<TenderInfo>\r\n						<Tender>\r\n							<TenderCode>cash</TenderCode>\r\n							<TenderSubCode>cashBack</TenderSubCode>\r\n						</Tender>\r\n						<TenderAmount>20.00</TenderAmount>\r\n						<ChangeFlag value=\"no\"/>\r\n					</TenderInfo>\r\n				</CheckCashDetail>\r\n			</FinancialEventDetail>\r\n		</FinancialEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n\r\n<nax:CheckCashDetail> \r\n<nax:CheckNumber> ... </nax:CheckNumber> [1]\r\n<nax:CheckCashFeeCollected> ... </nax:CheckCashFeeCollected> [1]\r\n<nax:TenderInfo> ... </nax:TenderInfo> [1..*]\r\n</nax:CheckCashDetail>\r\n\r\n<nax:CheckNumber> nax:id8N </nax:CheckNumber>\r\n\r\n<nax:CheckCashFeeCollected> nax:decimalValue8 </nax:CheckCashFeeCollected>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n\r\nIn POS-Journal33.xsd:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"FinancialEventDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:choice>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:BatchDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:CheckCashDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:DrawerLoanDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:DriveOffDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:PayInDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:PayOutDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:PriceOverrideDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:SafeDropDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:SafeLoanDetail\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:PumpTestDetail\"/>\r\n</xs:choice>\r\n<xs:attribute name=\"status\" use=\"required\">\r\n<xs:simpleType>\r\n<xs:restriction base=\"nax:id8\">\r\n<xs:enumeration value=\"normal\"/>\r\n<xs:enumeration value=\"cancel\"/>\r\n<xs:enumeration value=\"void\"/>\r\n</xs:restriction>\r\n</xs:simpleType>\r\n</xs:attribute>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"CheckCashDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:CheckNumber\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:CheckCashFeeCollected\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:TenderInfo\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n\r\nIn PBIDictionary33.xsd:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"CheckNumber\" type=\"nax:id8N\"/>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"CheckCashFeeCollected\" type=\"nax:decimalValue8\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\nAdditional Notes:\r\n\r\nThis really is a stand-alone event. In an instance document, it wouldn\'t ever be accompanied by any additional events. It is separate from any sales, refunds, voids, etc.\r\n\r\nThe only new elements are CheckCashDetail, CheckNumber, and CheckCashFeeCollected.  Also, CheckCashDetail can be tacked on to the end of the choices for FinancialEventDetail if this would be preferable.\r\n\r\nThe current set-up for TenderInfo is fine. For anything that is required that we don\'t have data for, we\'ll just put something generic in there to fill space. For example, it can be set up to only require certain information. Some stores may require more information about the customer than others.\r\n\r\nIf you think it would be better to use different base types for CheckNumber and CheckCashFeeCollected, that is fine.'),(139,'XML Document Example:\r\n---------------------\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\" xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\" xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<FinancialEvent>\r\n			<FinancialEventDetail status=\"normal\">\r\n				<DriveOffDetail>\r\n					<FuelGradeID>1</FuelGradeID>\r\n					<FuelPositionID>1</FuelPositionID>\r\n					<FuelGradeSalesVolume>4.5000</FuelGradeSalesVolume>\r\n					<FuelGradeSalesAmount>12.06</FuelGradeSalesAmount>\r\n					<LicensePlateID>1234567</LicensePlateID>\r\n					<VehicleColor>Blue</VehicleColor>\r\n					<VehicleType>SUV</VehicleType>\r\n				</DriveOffDetail>\r\n			</FinancialEventDetail>\r\n		</FinancialEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n----------------------------\r\n<nax:DriveOffDetail> \r\n<nax:FuelGradeID> ... </nax:FuelGradeID> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelPositionID> ... </nax:FuelPositionID> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume> ... </nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount> ... </nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount> [1]\r\n<nax:LicensePlateID> ... </nax:LicensePlateID> [0..1]\r\n<nax:VehicleDescription> ... </nax:VehicleDescription> [0..1]\r\n<nax:VehicleColor> ... </nax:VehicleColor> [0..1]\r\n<nax:VehicleType> ... </nax:VehicleType> [0..1]\r\n<nax:AuthorizingCashierID> ... </nax:AuthorizingCashierID> [0..1]\r\n<nax:LinkedTransactionInfo> ... </nax:LinkedTransactionInfo> [0..1]\r\n</nax:DriveOffDetail>\r\n\r\n<nax:VehicleColor> nax:description24 </nax:VehicleColor>\r\n\r\n<nax:VehicleType> nax:description24 </nax:VehicleType>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n--------------------------------\r\nIn POS-Journal33.xsd:\r\n---------------------\r\n<xs:element name=\"DriveOffDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelPositionID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:LicensePlateID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:VehicleDescription\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:VehicleColor\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:VehicleType\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:AuthorizingCashierID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:LinkedTransactionInfo\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n\r\nIn PBIDictionary33.xsd:\r\n-----------------------\r\n<xs:element name=\"VehicleColor\" type=\"nax:description24\"/>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"VehicleType\" type=\"nax:description24\"/>'),(140,'I couldn\'t see that this really needed to be a movement report (as was mentioned in the conference call) rather than a FinancialEvent in POSJournal, so here\'s my proposal.  If you okay this, you may want to close this CR out and create a new one for adding a MoneyOrderBatchDetail element to POSJournal.  You could set it as a child of this current CR, if this version of Mantis has that capability.\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Document Example:\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<FinancialEvent>\r\n			<--insert lots of required stuff here-->\r\n			<FinancialEventDetail status=\"normal\">\r\n				<MoneyOrderBatchDetail>\r\n					<TotalAmountRegular count=\"2\">25.00</TotalAmountRegular>\r\n					<TotalAmountVendor count=\"1\">15.00</TotalAmountVendor>\r\n					<TotalAmountFees>3.00</TotalAmountFees>\r\n					<BatchStatus>closed</BatchStatus>\r\n				</MoneyOrderBatchDetail>\r\n			</FinancialEventDetail>\r\n		</FinancialEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n\r\n<nax:MoneyOrderBatchDetail>\r\n<nax:TotalAmountRegular count=\"nax:count [1]\">  ... </nax:TotalAmountRegular> [1]\r\n<nax:TotalAmountVendor count=\"nax:count [1]\"> ... </nax:TotalAmountVendor> [1]\r\n<nax:TotalAmountFees> ... </nax:TotalAmountFees> [1]\r\n<nax:BatchStatus> ... </nax:BatchStatus> [1]\r\nModel group reference (not shown): nax:extension [1]\r\n</nax:MoneyOrderBatchDetail>\r\n\r\n<nax:TotalAmountRegular count=\"nax:count [1]\"> nax:amount12 </nax:TotalAmountRegular>\r\n\r\n<nax:TotalAmountVendor count=\"nax:count [1]\"> nax:amount12 </nax:TotalAmountVendor>\r\n\r\n<nax:TotalAmountFees> nax:amount12 </nax:TotalAmountFees>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"MoneyOrderBatchDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:TotalAmountRegular\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:TotalAmountVendor\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:TotalAmountFees\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:BatchStatus\"/>\r\n<xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TotalAmountRegular\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:simpleContent>\r\n<xs:extension base=\"nax:amount12\">\r\n<xs:attribute name=\"count\" type=\"nax:count\" use=\"required\"/>\r\n</xs:extension>\r\n</xs:simpleContent>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TotalAmountVendor\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:simpleContent>\r\n<xs:extension base=\"nax:amount12\">\r\n<xs:attribute name=\"count\" type=\"nax:count\" use=\"required\"/>\r\n</xs:extension>\r\n</xs:simpleContent>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TotalAmountFees\" type=\"nax:amount12\"/>'),(141,'Here is my updated proposal with more details, as requested. I will also enter this in as a CR for version 4.0, as requested.\r\n\r\nI have two different versions for you to consider.\r\n\r\nTotalAmount will be either in gallons or dollars, depending on the readingType. The units wouldn\'t need to be specified,  as the readingType makes the untis for TotalAmount implied.\r\n\r\nThis didn\'t really fit into a movement report. It\'s just an OtherEvent in POSJournal.\r\n\r\nXML Document Example:\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<OtherEvent>\r\n			<--Insert many required elements here-->\r\n			<DispenserMeterDetail readingType=\"Pure Volume\">\r\n				<FuelPositionID>1</FuelPositionID>\r\n				<FuelGradeID>1</FuelGradeID>\r\n				<TotalAmount>999.999</TotalAmount>\r\n			</DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n		</OtherEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n\r\n<nax:DispenserMeterDetail readingType=\"nax:description24 [1]\">\r\n<nax:FuelPositionID>  ... </nax:FuelPositionID> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeID> ... </nax:FuelGradeID> [1]\r\n<nax:TotalAmount> ... </nax:TotalAmount> [1]\r\nModel group reference (not shown): nax:extension [0..1]\r\n</nax:DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n\r\n<nax:TotalAmount> nax:decimalValue8 </nax:TotalAmount>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"DispenserMeterDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelPositionID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:TotalAmount\"/>\r\n<xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:attribute name=\"readingType\" type=\"nax:description24\" use=\"required\"/>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TotalAmount\" type=\"nax:decimalValue8\"/>\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nAlternatively, it could be done this way (with FuelGradeSalesAmount holding the amount for reading type \'Sale Amount\',  FuelGradeSalesVolume holding the amount for reading type \'Sale Volume\', and FuelProductVolume holding the amount for  reading type \'Pure Volume\', eliminating the need for the reading type to be stored, as it is a choice between these  three amounts):\r\n\r\nXML Document Example:\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<NAXML-POSJournal xmlns=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16\"  xmlns:xsi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance\"  xsi:schemaLocation=\"http://www.naxml.org/POSBO/Vocabulary/2003-10-16 NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd\" version=\"3.3\" release=\"4\">\r\n	<TransmissionHeader>\r\n		<StoreLocationID>746</StoreLocationID>\r\n		<VendorName>The Pinnacle Corporation</VendorName>\r\n		<VendorModelVersion>Palm v8.4</VendorModelVersion>\r\n	</TransmissionHeader>\r\n	<JournalReport>\r\n		<JournalHeader>\r\n			<ReportSequenceNumber>1</ReportSequenceNumber>\r\n			<PrimaryReportPeriod interval=\"other\">1</PrimaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<SecondaryReportPeriod>0</SecondaryReportPeriod>\r\n			<BeginDate>2005-08-17</BeginDate>\r\n			<BeginTime>14:43:00</BeginTime>\r\n			<EndDate>2005-08-17</EndDate>\r\n			<EndTime>14:43:30</EndTime>\r\n		</JournalHeader>\r\n		<OtherEvent>\r\n			<--Insert many required elements here-->\r\n			<DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n				<FuelPositionID>1</FuelPositionID>\r\n				<FuelGradeID>1</FuelGradeID>\r\n				<FuelGradeSalesVolume>999.999</FuelGradeSalesVolume>\r\n			</DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n		</OtherEvent>\r\n	</JournalReport>\r\n</NAXML-POSJournal>\r\n\r\n\r\nXML Instance Representation:\r\n\r\n<nax:DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n<nax:FuelPositionID>  ... </nax:FuelPositionID> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeID> ... </nax:FuelGradeID> [1]\r\nStart Choice [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount> ... </nax:FuelGradeSalesAmount> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume> ... </nax:FuelGradeSalesVolume> [1]\r\n<nax:FuelProductVolume> ... </nax:FuelProductVolume> [1]\r\nEnd Choice\r\nModel group reference (not shown): nax:extension [0..1]\r\n</nax:DispenserMeterDetail>\r\n\r\n\r\nSchema Component Representation:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"DispenserMeterDetail\">\r\n<xs:complexType>\r\n<xs:sequence>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelPositionID\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"nax:FuelGradeID\"/>\r\n<xs:choice>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"FuelGradeSalesAmount\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"FuelGradeSalesVolume\"/>\r\n<xs:element ref=\"FuelProductVolume\"/>\r\n</xs:choice>\r\n<xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n</xs:sequence>\r\n</xs:complexType>\r\n</xs:element>'),(142,'Ignore the first attached file. If I could delete it, I would. There was a missing ! in the comment line that messed the whole thing up. I fixed that.'),(143,'Have added xml examples of what I believe the use cases should be.  This will need to be changed for 3.3.3 and 3.3.4.'),(144,'Resolution: Add VehicleColor and VehicleType as optional elements below VehicleDescription and revise the annotation for VehicleDescription to denote is as free-form text.'),(145,'Returned to Heather for more detail'),(146,'Resolution: Revise the refund and void event use cases as Paul suggests in 3.3.3 and 3.3.4 conformance test use cases.'),(147,'Returned to user for feedback - sample XML document.'),(148,'See attached file. Doesn’t follow the standard just to give an idea.'),(149,'I uploaded 2 files. One is a sample schema for MoneyOrderBatchDetail. The other is a sample XML document. \r\n\r\nHere is what would be added to the NAXML schemas:\r\n\r\nIn NAXML-POSJournal33.xsd:\r\n<xs:element name=\"MoneyOrderBatchDetail\"> \r\n   <xs:annotation> \r\n      <xs:documentation>Money Order Batch information</xs:documentation> \r\n   </xs:annotation> \r\n   <xs:complexType> \r\n      <xs:sequence> \r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:BatchNumber\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:MoneyOrderType\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:MoneyOrderFeesTotalAmount\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:BatchStatus\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:NetworkID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:BatchCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n      </xs:sequence> \r\n   </xs:complexType> \r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n \r\nIn NAXML-PBIDictionary33.xsd:\r\n<xs:element name=\"MoneyOrderType\">\r\n   <xs:complexType> \r\n      <xs:sequence>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:MoneyOrderCount\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n         <xs:element ref=\"nax:MoneyOrderFeeCollected\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n      </xs:sequence>\r\n      <xs:attribute name=\"type\" use=\"required\">\r\n         <xs:simpleType>\r\n            <xs:restriction base=\"xs:string\">\r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"moneyOrder\"/>\r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"giftCertificate\"/> \r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"payroll\"/> \r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"paidOut\"/> \r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"transfer\"/> \r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"void\"/>\r\n               <xs:enumeration value=\"other\"/> \r\n            </xs:restriction>\r\n         </xs:simpleType>\r\n      </xs:attribute>\r\n   </xs:complexType> \r\n</xs:element>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"MoneyOrderCount\" type=\"nax:count\"/>\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"MoneyOrderFeesTotalAmount\" type=\"nax:amount12\"/>\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\nInstead of putting the enumeration in that schema, the \"type\" attribute for \"MoneyOrderType\" could be set to \'type=\"moneyOrderType\"\' and the following added to NAXML-PBIBaseTypes33.xsd:\r\n<xs:simpleType name=\"moneyOrderType\">\r\n   <xs:union memberTypes=\"nax:moneyOrderTypeBase nax:id40\"/>\r\n</xs:simpleType>\r\n\r\n<xs:simpleType name=\"moneyOrderTypeBase\">\r\n   <xs:restriction base=\"nax:id40\">\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"moneyOrder\"/>\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"giftCertificate\"/> \r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"payroll\"/> \r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"paidOut\"/> \r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"transfer\"/> \r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"void\"/>\r\n      <xs:enumeration value=\"other\"/> \r\n   </xs:restriction>\r\n</xs:simpleType>\r\n\r\nI\'m not sure that NetworkID would ever be needed by anyone, but since it is one of the existing elements used in a regular BatchDetail, I went ahead and included it in here, just in case.\n\nedited on: 09-29-05 11:52'),(150,'09/29/2005 - Teleconference attendees agreed with this change.  Assigned to Paul Kern for updating the schema.'),(151,'09/29/2005 - Teleconference attendees agree the change is backward compatible.  SecondaryReportPeriod will be affected also.'),(152,'The node has not been changed to MixMatchPrice. MixMatchPrice is one of the choices for that node. Under the MixMatchEntry element we have a choice of \"MixMatchPrice\", \"MixMatchDiscountAmount\", and \"MixMatchDiscountPercent\". \r\n\r\nIn the scenario Peter describes, I agree the \"MixMatchPrice\" should be used.'),(153,'09/29/2005 Teleconference - Mr. Godwin, Mr. Peele, and Mr. Wade agree this is a desirable change.  \r\n\r\nRecommended approach - create a checkDigit attribute with enumerated values of \"present\", \"absent\".  Update the annotation for POSCodeFormat to indicate the selection of a particular value for POSCodeFormat does not necessarily indicate whether a check digit will be included or excluded on the barcode number in POSCode.'),(154,'It is agreed that the MixMatchDiscountAmount should be the total discount, but Mr. Steele suggests we look into how to communicate whether a discounted price applies in cases where a quantity less than the match quantity is purchased (new CR for version 4).'),(155,'DiscountReason is of type nax:discountReason, which is a union of nax:discountReasonBase (an enumerated type) with nax:id16, which allows any value of up to 16 characters.  The group has no objection to using nax:id40 instead of nax:id16.'),(156,'In the Technical Specification dated September 5, 2005, both of these use cases are designated as non-core. New use cases for fuel grade price maintenance by grade, rather than by fueling position were added as core use cases.'),(157,'The conformance tool is only looking for two optional elements - TankDescription and TankVolume.  The Working Group decided that TankVolume should be required v. TankDepth.'),(158,'Change assignment to Paul Kern from John Hervey. This is now a function of the schema editing committee.'),(159,'Change to Conformance Tool is in progress. (10/17/2005)'),(160,'Completed'),(161,'This should be transferred to the schema editing committee.'),(162,'This should be transferred to the schema editing committee.'),(163,'Change made to schemea 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern of Scema Editing Committee'),(164,'Change made 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern of Schema editing committee'),(165,'Schmeas changed 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern of Schema Editing committee.'),(166,'Schema changed 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern of Schema editing committee'),(167,'Base type of nax:reportPeriod changed to have string max length 12 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern'),(168,'Question about the annotation change approved.  Are we saying that the prescense of the checkdigit attribute has no meaning?  Need some clarification before we can change schema.'),(169,'Annotation of MixMatchDiscountAmount  changed to read \"The total money amount discount to apply to this group.\"  on 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern'),(170,'Changed  nax:discountReason to be  a union of nax:discountReasonBase (an enumerated type) with nax:id40, was union with nax:id16. Changed 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern'),(171,'This appears to have already be done.  The version attribute was not fixed on any of the docs.  release attribute was missing on NAXML-MovementReport so I did add that.  2005-10-26 - Paul Kern'),(172,'Schema changed 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern of Schema editing committee'),(173,'This appears to have already be done. The version attribute was not fixed on any of the docs. release attribute was missing on NAXML-MovementReport so I did add that. 2005-10-26 - Paul Kern'),(174,'Changed nax:discountReason to be a union of nax:discountReasonBase (an enumerated type) with nax:id40, was union with nax:id16. Changed 2005-10-26 by Paul Kern'),(175,'Change was made to the 3.3.4-4 version of the schemas'),(176,'Change made to 3.3.4-4 version of schemas'),(177,'Change made to 3.3.4-4 version of schemas'),(178,'Change made to 3.3.4-4 version of schemas'),(179,'Change made to 3.3.4-4 version of schemas'),(180,'Question about the annotation change approved. Are we saying that the prescense of the checkdigit attribute has no meaning? Need some clarification before we can change schema.'),(181,'In an instance document, each item could fall into one of three cases (in this list, the \"format\" attribute, e.g., \"ean13\", could have any of the allowed values, irrelevant for the discussion below):\r\n  1. <POSCodeFormat format==\"ean13\" checkDigit=\"present\"/>\r\n  2. <POSCodeFormat format==\"ean13\" checkDigit=\"absent\">\r\n  3. <POSCodeFormat format==\"ean13\">\r\n\r\nIn example 1, the producer of the document is declaring that the right-most digit of the associated POSCode is, without doubt, a check digit.\r\n\r\nIn example 2, the producer of the document is declaring that the right-most digit of the associated POSCode is, without doubt, *not* a check digit (one would need to be calculated by the receiving system as needed).\r\n\r\nIn example 3, the producer of the document has chosen not to declare the status of the right-most digit of the associated POSCode (this is the backward-compatibility case).  Therefore, the receiving system treats the right-most digit in an implementation-defined manner, most likely one that was previously established with the producer of the document.\r\n\r\nPlease note that the value of the \"format\" attribute should be documented in the schema as \"does not necessarily indicate whether a check digit will be included or excluded on the number in POSCode\".\r\n\r\nThe checkDigit attribute is the primary determiner of whether a check digit is present in the POSCode.  If the checkDigit attribute is absent, then the receiving system is free to make assumptions regarding the presence of the checkDigit based on secondary (other) factors, possibly including the value of the POSCodeFormat \"format\" attribute (although this practice should be discouraged).\r\n\r\nedited on: 10-27-05 10:11\r\n\r\nedited on: 10-27-05 10:12\n\nedited on: 10-27-05 13:30'),(182,'This change request only address the \"initialize\" use case.  The same content model exists in the \"Add/Change\" use case.  Is the intention that in both use cases \"MerchandiseCode should be made optional??  I won\'t take any action until this is resolved.'),(183,'2005-10-31 Added optional checkDigit attribute to POSCodeFormat in pbi dictionary.  Attribute is a string with enumeration of present and absent.   Included in the 334-5 schemas.'),(184,'ItemLine/Promotion was made unbounded in version 3.3.4 and appears to address these requirements.'),(185,'Requirements may be address via the use of ItemLine/Promotion.'),(186,'No response was received with respect to what document and content model this was to be added to.  Request therefore is refused.'),(187,'Refused by working group with a recommendation to submitter that FGMDetail structure be used as an extension of a POSJournal transaction.'),(188,'Mr. Steele and Ms. Kinney will develop a better content model and resubmit.'),(189,'Yes it is the intention that in both the \"initialize\" and \"add/change\" use cases \"MerchandiseCode should be made optional.\r\n\r\nThis was discussed and agreed to in the 11/4/05 face to face meeting.'),(190,'Discussed in 2005-11-03 face to face meeting.  Decided that it should be moved to 4.0.  Seperate CR already filed for 4.0, so closing this one.'),(191,'The conformance tool developer has been notified to make the change to both use cases.'),(192,'This is a duplicate of 136'),(193,'Bill Wade and David Ezell concur that DiscountCount and PromotionCount should contain the number of items discounted in most cases, but that this may vary depending on the context in which the elements are used.'),(194,'Please review change request 98 and provide feedback on Heather Kinney\'s Aug 19 proposal.'),(195,'Discussed in 2006-01-05 teleconference.  Tabled until the 2006-01-19 teleconference when we discuss the version numbering of 3.3.4 vs. 3.4.0'),(196,'Deferred to 2006-01-19 teleconference when we discuss version numbering.'),(197,'2006-01-05 teleconference participants agreed to update the annotation for these two elements to indicate that they should contain the number of items discounted rather than the number of transactions.'),(198,'Completed by John Hervey'),(199,'Completed and tested per John Hervey'),(200,'See Change Request 0000071.  It is basically the same issue.'),(201,'The journal Header needs to be reworked as well. Not all POS Systems today work with Primary and Secondary Reporting Periods. It is quite common that the transactions are identified by POS number and POS shift number. There should be the possibility to use either Day number (Primary Reporting Period) and site-wide-shift number (Secondary Reporting Period) or just POS number and POS shift number.'),(202,'Sorry, by accident I\'ve chosen the wrong Document. The request is for NAXML-POSJournal'),(203,'Change made 2006-01-30 to Dictionary:  Change TransactionID from nax: id8 to nax:id16 by Paul Kern.  Included in 334-6 set of schemas'),(204,'completed 2006-01-30'),(205,'2006-01-30 - Paul Kern - Changed annotations to reflect that they refer to item counts.  Included in the 334-6 set of schemas.'),(206,'Here is what I propose.  This is not backwards compatible to 3.3.4.  However, since 3.4 is not officially released does it matter?  The file that is attached above is the 3.4 maintenance schema with this change included for review.\r\n\r\n <xs:element name=\"TaxStrategyMaintenance\">\r\n      <xs:annotation>\r\n         <xs:documentation>Tax Strategy Maintenance (TST) – Contains those data elements,\r\nwhich need to be sent from the BO to the POS system to maintain methods and algorithms for the application of tax to\r\nitems/merchandise code/fuel grade.</xs:documentation>\r\n      </xs:annotation>\r\n      <xs:complexType>\r\n         <xs:sequence>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TableAction\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyID\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyDescription\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TSTDetail\" minOccurs=\"0\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n         </xs:sequence>\r\n      </xs:complexType>\r\n   </xs:element>\r\n   <xs:element name=\"TSTDetail\">\r\n      <xs:complexType>\r\n         <xs:sequence>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelID\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelSequenceID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n         </xs:sequence>\r\n      </xs:complexType>\r\n   </xs:element>\n\nedited on: 02-24-06 19:06'),(208,'I\'d recommend we make TaxLevelID unbounded, add to it an optional taxSequenceID attribute, and deprecate the optional TaxSequenceID element.  That would be more backward compatible.'),(209,'Steve Straley raised this issue...'),(210,'PayInReason and PayOutReason are each defined as the union of an enumerated base type with the id16 base type.  They should therefore accept any value in the enumeration, plus any other value that conforms to the id16 base type.\r\n\r\nNote, however, that the use of the enumerated values is recommended to improve interoperability.  If you have payin/payout reason codes that are not present in the enumeration, a change request to add them would be helpful...'),(211,'The absence of TenderInfo from the refund use case sounds like an oversight.  A revision of the use case seems be indicated.'),(212,'Example of what I believe is the Bill Wade recommendation for changing TaxLevelId to unbounded in Tax Strategy Detail.  This will be included in Version 3.4.1 of the schemas.  Schema will look like this:\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TSTDetail\">\r\n      <xs:complexType>\r\n         <xs:sequence>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyID\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelID\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelSequenceID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyDescription\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n         </xs:sequence>\r\n      </xs:complexType>\r\n   </xs:element>\r\n\r\nDefinition of TaxLevelID would look like this: (Optional Attribute of axLevelSequenceID would be added)\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TaxLevelID\">\r\n      <xs:annotation>\r\n         <xs:documentation>A pointer to the Tax Level Table. The values of the table specify the tax level being reported. </xs:documentation>\r\n      </xs:annotation>\r\n      <xs:complexType>\r\n         <xs:simpleContent>\r\n            <xs:extension base=\"nax:id4\">\r\n               <xs:attribute name=\"TaxLevelSequenceID\" type=\"nax:id8\" use=\"optional\"/>\r\n            </xs:extension>\r\n         </xs:simpleContent>\r\n      </xs:complexType>\r\n   </xs:element>\n\nedited on: 03-16-06 15:20'),(214,'Working group agrees that this is a conformance tool issue.  Any payIn/PayOut reason code should be valid.'),(215,'One minor correction.  The new attribute name should start with a lower case letter, to wit: taxLevelSequenceID.  WIth that change, members present at the 3/30/2006 teleconference agreed to accept the recommendation below.  This change CAN be included in version 3.4.0, since that version is still in public comment stage.\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TSTDetail\">\r\n      <xs:complexType>\r\n         <xs:sequence>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:RecordAction\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyID\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelID\" maxOccurs=\"unbounded\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxLevelSequenceID\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:element ref=\"nax:TaxStrategyDescription\" minOccurs=\"0\"/>\r\n            <xs:group ref=\"nax:extension\"/>\r\n         </xs:sequence>\r\n      </xs:complexType>\r\n   </xs:element>\r\n\r\nDefinition of TaxLevelID would look like this: (Optional Attribute of axLevelSequenceID would be added)\r\n\r\n<xs:element name=\"TaxLevelID\">\r\n      <xs:annotation>\r\n         <xs:documentation>A pointer to the Tax Level Table. The values of the table specify the tax level being reported. </xs:documentation>\r\n      </xs:annotation>\r\n      <xs:complexType>\r\n         <xs:simpleContent>\r\n            <xs:extension base=\"nax:id4\">\r\n               <xs:attribute name=\"taxLevelSequenceID\" type=\"nax:id8\" use=\"optional\"/>\r\n            </xs:extension>\r\n         </xs:simpleContent>\r\n      </xs:complexType>\r\n   </xs:element>\n\nedited on: 03-30-06 15:08'),(216,'Paul Kern 2006-05-16 Made changes as indicated above.  Changed TSTDetail/TaxLevelID to maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" in maintenance, and Added optional attribute taxLevelSequenceID to TaxLevelID in dictionary.  New schemeas pacackaged into NAXML POSBOS 341.zip file available on jotspot'),(217,'Paul Kern 2006-05-16 Made changes as indicated above.  Changed TSTDetail/TaxLevelID to maxOccurs=\"unbounded\" in maintenance, and Added optional attribute taxLevelSequenceID to TaxLevelID in dictionary.  New schemeas pacackaged into NAXML POSBOS 341.zip file available on jotspot'),(218,'Added 3.4.1 to enumeration of pointRelease in NAXML-PBIBaseTypes34.xsd  Uploaded new schemas to jotspot'),(219,'David Ezell recommends maxOccurs=\"2\" on the Depth/Volume choices.  That would permit both to be passed.'),(220,'Per David Ezell, use of nillable on required elements and attributes would address this need.  Each element and attribute should be reviewed with respect to nillability.'),(221,'Per David Godwin, a checklist should be created for the creation of new items.  He will start one.'),(222,'David Ezell seconds this request, and recommends the use of http:POST instead of GET when comms occur over http.'),(223,'Vaughan Hunt recommends including the ability to request POSJournal reports.\n\nedited on: 03-15-07 14:42'),(224,'Some method of choreography is required, but a semaphore file may or may not be the optimal method.'),(225,'David Ezell and Heather Kinney seconded this request.'),(226,'The provision for an ItemAdd document which will require the MerchandiseCode and an ItemChange document which will not can address this issue.'),(227,'The tender codes will be reworked in version 4.0 to eliminate the open-ended enumeration.'),(228,'Heather Kinney seconds this request.'),(229,'Added a checklist item to the element/attribute design checklist to review the use of the sign on signed values.'),(230,'NAXML does not prohibit the use of UTF-16 encoding in instance documents.  The instance document must, however, declare the encoding used in the <?xml> directive.'),(231,'More details are necessary with respect to where exchange rates need to be provided.'),(232,'Implies a corresponding change to POSJournal'),(233,'Conformance tool updated to use 3.4.1 schemas.'),(234,'Ivan and I have been discussing this issue.  \r\n\r\nWe would like to propose that the FuelPrepayLine be discontinued and that fuel prepays use the FuelLine but with an additional optional status flag indicating that this was a fuel prepay.\r\n\r\nThis will allow the additional data elements (particularly discounts) currently unavailable on the FuelPrepayLine to be passed to the BOS.'),(235,'Chevron uses fuel prepays in a number of markets.  The current NAXML journal records created by the POS do not support discounts for pre-pay transactions.  \r\n\r\nRather than enhancing the FuelPrepay record, Chevron propose to overcome this limitation by using the FuelLine record for both prepay and postpay fuel sales. One additional optional Boolean would be added to the fuelLine record so that the BOS can recognise the sale as a prepay.\r\n\r\nChevron’s expectation would be that this enhancement is introduced in NAXML 4.0. Chevron may also apply this change to it’s NAXML 3.4 implementation to support our business needs\n\nedited on: 05-08-07 20:51'),(236,'As part of the discusssion for 4.0 changes, I\'ve included this example of an under-dispensed prepay in Radiant\'s implementation\r\n\r\n<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\r\n<SaleEvent uuid=\"\">\r\n			<EventSequenceID>1</EventSequenceID> \r\n			<TrainingModeFlag value=\"no\" /> \r\n			<CashierID>1000000225</CashierID> \r\n			<RegisterID>1</RegisterID> \r\n			<TillID>1</TillID> \r\n			<OutsideSalesFlag value=\"no\" /> \r\n			<TransactionID>662</TransactionID> \r\n			<EventStartDate>2005-07-05</EventStartDate> \r\n			<EventStartTime>14:53:20</EventStartTime> \r\n			<EventEndDate>2005-07-05</EventEndDate> \r\n			<EventEndTime>14:53:40</EventEndTime> \r\n			<BusinessDate>2005-07-05</BusinessDate> \r\n			<ReceiptDate>2005-07-05</ReceiptDate> \r\n			<ReceiptTime>14:53:40</ReceiptTime> \r\n			<Offlin